title: RAZZO a marca que brilha e perfuma seu lar!
description:
Lançamento do novo logo da marca Razzo e novas embalagens
Os produtos da Razzo são conhecidos dos brasileiros há 48 anos. Fundada em 1964, por Salvador Razzo, em São Paulo, a companhia iniciou suas atividades com a produção de matérias-primas utilizadas na fabricação de produtos de limpeza e higiene.  Ao longo de sua história, a empresa diversificou suas atividades, dedicando-se, primeiramente, à produção e à  comercialização de sabão em barra e, posteriormente, aos mercados cosmético, farmacêutico e químico. Site: www.razzo.com.br.

title: 50 Jahre Leifheit - Leifheit im Wandel der Zeit (die Werbeklassiker)
description:
Zusammenschnitt von Leifheit Werbespots der letzten fünfzig Jahre mit vielen Klassikern. 

Im Jahr 1959 gründeten Ingeborg und Günter Leifheit die Günter LEIFHEIT KG in Nassau zur Produktion von Teppichkehrern und Bodenwischern. 1972 wurde das Unternehmen von der ITT, New York, übernommen.

Schon als das Ehepaar Leifheit die Marke LEIFHEIT vor nunmehr einem halben Jahrhundert aufbaute, stand ein Aspekt im Vordergrund: nicht allein die Produktidee, sondern der Produktnutzen ist der entscheidende Aspekt für den Erfolg.

Technik, Ergonomie und Qualität bilden bei LEIFHEIT von jeher eine ästhetische Einheit und führen zu kreativen Problemlösungen, die das Leben erleichtern. Eben deshalb sind LEIFHEIT-Produkte seit 50 Jahren „immer eine Idee besser" und machen das Leben zu Hause Tag für Tag ein Stück leichter, komfortabler und schöner.

Seit 1984 ist LEIFHEIT eine börsennotierte Aktiengesellschaft. Das Unternehmen zählt heute mit den bekannten Marken LEIFHEIT, Soehnle und Dr. Oetker Backgeräte sowie den französischen Tochtergesellschaften Birambeau und Herby zu den führenden europäischen Anbietern von Haushaltsprodukten.

Das Unternehmen mit Hauptsitz in Nassau/Lahn beschäftigt rund 1.200 Mitarbeiter.

title: El Mejor Trabajo del Mundo   P G Juegos Olímpicos de London 2012 - YouTube.flv
description:
Mercadotecnia Emocional 
Sin lugar a dudas la Mercadotecnia Emocional ha llegado para quedarse, la muestra está en la publicidad y propaganda premiada a lo largo del mundo que ha logrado incrementar las ventas de productos de valor agregado y triplicar las recaudaciones de fondos para organizaciones civiles. En el rol de compra nuestra mente y su racionalidad han quedado superadas por la fuerza y pasión de las emociones, es por esto que hemos incluido en los programas de Adiestramiento y Capacitación para Comerciantes y Fuerzas de Ventas de las empresas más grandes de México la Mercadotecnia Emocional y su impacto en el Rol de Compra. El Dr. Abraham Nosnik nos dice que la Comunicación debe de ser Íntegra, Integral e Integrada, así son nuestros consumidores y ciudadanos por lo tanto nuestra responsabilidad es mayor. 
Pedro Rodríguez Reynaga 
Junio 2012

title: G.I.Joe Marvel comics animation commercial Pt1
description:
This is part 1 of the original cartoon animations used for the G.I.Joe Marvel comic run.  I haven't found these on youtube yet and I have always wanted to give back for all that I have taken.  Here it is!  

It is because of the initial cartoon commercials for the comics which created the demand for the daily series which was good but not as good as it could had been if it was produced along the same principles as these 30 second commercials.  I fell in love with G.I.Joe with the help of these commercials.  They were brilliant and still are after 25 years!  

After waiting 25 years, I wish the new live action movie would live up to the exciting standards set by this groundbreaking series!  Instead, the new G.I.Joe "Rise of Cobra" seems to be rewriting things as they go along.  So much for progress.  What I have on youtube is what I feel is G.I.Joe.  I hope everyone will agree!

YO JOE!!!!

title: Sesame Street - The Most Important Meal of the Day
description: The Most Important Meal of the Day is a Sesame Street song from 1993 performed mainly by the Anything Muppets. A young boy (Peter Linz) is indignant about eating breakfast; he'd rather play. Out of nowhere, a chef (Julianne Buescher) appears and is shocked by what she hears. In an upbeat gospel song, she sings about the importance of breakfast, with a montage of people and Muppets enjoying their meal, including a tiger, a horse, Ernie, Elmo, Telly, Barkley, and Big Bird. The boy is convinced by what he hears, and asks his mother what's for breakfast. Performers (other than those noted above) include Lisa Buckley (as the boy's mother), Jim Martin, Alice Dinnean-Vernon, Fran Brill, Joey Mazzarino, and David Rudman. This song was written by Tony Geiss and directed by Lisa Simon.

title: ShamWow Commercial (FULL)
description:
You'll be saying WOW every time!

This is Vince Shlomi, AKA Vince Offer, AKA The ShamWOW guy in his debut as a TV pitchman.

If you were interested enough to watch this video then I think you will like this one:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZsQcyhBsSjI
It's the entire dialogue of the Shamwow commercial made into a song. It's not my video or anything, I just think it's awesome.

The Shamwow was not an original idea... In fact Billy Mays was pitching a similar product before Vince was on the scene. Check out Billy Mays' Zorbeez here:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fdmbLZKaCpM

title: 1990-luvun parhaita suomalaisia mainoksia (Osa 4/5)
description:
MTV3: KAIKKIEN AIKOJEN PARHAAT SEKUNNIT (HISTORY OF FINNISH TV COMMERCIALS) 

Kaikkien aikojen parhaat sekunnit on ohjelmasarja, johon on koottu suosituimpia mainoselokuvia 1950-luvulta 2000-luvulle. Ohjelmassa nähtävät mainokset on palkittu Mainos-Oskareilla, Kultaisilla Klaffeilla, Voitto-palkinnoilla tai muilla vastaavilla tunnustuksilla. Lisäksi mukaan on poimittu omien vuosikymmentensä muistetuimpia ja puhutuimpia mainoselokuvia. 

Osa 4/5; 1990-luku  
Laman jälkeen suomalaisuus palasi kaiken kulttuurin kärkeen, mainontaankin. Maitolaiturit, tanssilavat ja järvenrannat... Tuhlaajapoika palasi kotiin, jokaisessa asui pieni lehmä, oltiin loman tarpeessa ja etsittiin Teukkaa. 

Tuotanto: © Pohjantähti-Elokuva Oy (2007) 
Ohjelma kuuluu MTV3:n 50v. juhlavuoden ohjelmistoon.

description:

Nothing will stop them. The mini kitchen goes where others never dare to go. Within minutes everything is set up outside a busy station and ready to feed the masses. 

Recipes include, delicious Chicken with Wholegrain and Quinoa, a veggie Mixed Bean and Five Whole Grain Salad and a protein packed Grilled Salmon with Wholegrain Quinoa Tomato and Basil.

Um grupo de grandes amigos estão fartos das suas vidas adultas: Adam (John Cusack) foi deixado pela namorada; Lou (Rob Corddry) é um noctívago sem rumo; a mulher de Nick (Craig Robinson) controla-o a todo o momento e o viciado em videojogos Jacob (Clark Duke) nem consegue sair de casa. Depois de uma noite de bebidas no jacuzzi do resort de esqui, o grupo acorda, com uma grande ressaca, de volta ao ano de 1986. title: L'anno in cui i miei genitori andarono in vacanza
description: Nel 1970 il Brasile e il mondo intero sembrano essere sconvolti, ma la più grande preoccupazione del dodicenne Mauro non ha niente a che vedere con le dittature militari: il suo sogno più grande è vedere il Brasile vincere la Coppa del Mondo per la terza volta. A causa della loro militanza politica, i genitori di Mauro decidono di lasciarlo per un periodo al nonno Mòtel, al quale però è successo qualcosa di inaspettato. Sarà il vicino del nonno, lanziano e solitario Shlomo, a prendersi cura del bambino. Linaspettata convivenza svela a entrambi un mondo fino ad allora sconosciuto...

title: RETRO CLASSIC TV COMMERCIAL - 1950s - LIVE BETTER ELECTRICALLY (GE THEATER)
description:
***used in the May 5,2010 episode of  Comedy Central's "Colbert Report" *** ---"Live Better Electrically" was a slogan used in the late 1950's by the General Electric Company and local electric power companies to promote Electrical Living, primarily focused at rural communities and farms that still hadn't been connected to the power grid, as well as new housing developments fitted with all-electric heating and cooling, kitchens, and appliances. These new homes were "Medallion Homes", and displayed a plaque showing that fact.

This presentation features clips from a 1957 "General Electric Theater", hosted by Ronald Reagan, and also includes the then-popular jingle, as well as idyllic print advertising stills from GE, faboulous UPA-inspired 50's animation, and includes a final period ad which, in today's modern society, looks completely outrageous...but it is our history!

title: Audi Q5 Tv Spot  2010
description:
http://www.pbn.ro http://www.pbv2.ro http://www.porschetimisoara.ro Noul Audi Q5:
sportiv si flexibil

•SUV-ul de performanţă de la Audi ridică ştacheta 
•Tehnologii inovative pentru o conducere dinamică
•Interior spaţios cu o multitudine de funcţii inteligente


Ingolstadt  Noul Audi Q5 combină dinamismul unei berline sport cu un interior extrem de variabil si opţiuni flexibile pentru utilizarea în timpul liber şi împreună cu familia. Motoarele puternice şi eficiente, tracţiunea integrală quattro permanentă şi mecanismul de rulare agil au fost combinate pentru crearea unui pachet tehnologic superior, atât pentru conducerea pe teren normal, cât şi pe teren accidentat. Funcţiile de ultimă generaţie, precum transmisia S tronic cu şapte trepte de viteză şi dublu ambreiaj şi sistemul de control „Audi drive select, sunt dovezi ale sloganului Audi Vorsprung durch Technik (Progres prin tehnologie). Cel mai sportiv SUV din clasa sa este dinamic, multifuncţional si confortabil.

Dimensiunile indică faptul că acesta este un SUV de proporţii complet noi. Având o lungime de 4,63 m (15,19 ft) şi o lăţime de 1,88 m (6,17 ft), noul Audi Q5 are o înălţime de numai 1,65 m (5,41 ft)  fiind un model mai sportiv decât toţi concurenţii săi. Mai mult, acest SUV stabileşte un alt punct de referinţă în clasa sa, având un coeficient aerodinamic scăzut de 0,33.

Cu eleganţa sa sportivă şi formele sculptate cu măiestrie, designul noului Q5 se îmbină perfect cu caracterul mărcii Audi. Partea frontală este dominată de faruri expresive în ambele părţi ale grilei mari formate dintr-un singur cadru; la cerere, acestea pot fi înlocuite cu faruri bi-xenon şi lumini diurne cu LED-uri. Privit din lateral, roţile mari şi marginile ridicate sunt dotări extrem de remarcabile.

title: KFSN-TV - Affiliation Switch promos - 1985
description:
This is a set of four 30-second spots promoting KFSN-TV's (Fresno, Ca.) switch from CBS to ABC in September 1985.  These promos were originally on TV-Ark.

The first three spots feature KFSN anchors John Wallace, Dan Taylor (sports), and Nancy Osborne, while the fourth promotes a "premiere party" featuring the airing of the "Dynasty" pilot movie, and a locally-produced special.  It's probably safe to say KFSN's final CBS broadcast was the Sept. 8, 1985 airing of "60 Minutes".

The switch was necessitated when KFSN's parent, Capital Cities Communications, purchased ABC.  Fresno's previous ABC affiliate, KJEO-TV (now KGPE) picked up CBS.  John Wallace now works at KGPE, while Dan Taylor and Nancy Osborne are still at KFSN.

Copyright 1985 KFSN-TV/ABC, Inc.

S.Pellegrino and Missoni have the pleasure to unveil today the first Special Edition bottle born from the collaboration of two famous Italian brands in the world under the red star of S.Pellegrino Italian Talents international project.
Chef Massimo Bottura will delight the guests with its extraordinary culinary creations as highest expression of Italian Talents in fine dining. Bellavista wine will complete the soirée with their unique flavor of Italian excellence.
S.Pellegrino has launched a new international project dedicated to the ITALIAN TALENTS, aimed at creating significant synergies among Italian companies of worldwide renown that operate in the upper bracket of the market and express Italian culture and style, distinguishing themselves for innovation, quality, service, design and prestige. With this initiative, S.Pellegrino offers and shows to the world the best side of Italy, the part that everybody abroad appreciates and loves.

http://www.foodandtourism.com/video/142.html 

S.Pellegrino e Missoni presentano oggi la prima bottiglia in Edizione Speciale nata dalla collaborazione fra due dei più celebri brand italiani nell'ambito del nuovo progetto internazionale ITALIAN TALENTS.
Nel corso dell'anteprima, lo chef Massimo Bottura delizierà gli ospiti con le sue straordinarie creazioni gastronomiche che testimoniano il vero talento italiano in cucina. I vini Bellavista, fra le massime eccellenze italiane in campo enologico, accompagneranno la degustazione.
S.Pellegrino annuncia il lancio del nuovo progetto internazionale dedicato ai "talenti italiani" ideato con l'obiettivo di creare importanti sinergie con aziende italiane di reputazione internazionale, che operano nella fascia più alta del mercato ed esprimono la cultura e lo stile italiani, distinguendosi per innovazione, qualità, servizio, design e prestigio. Con questa iniziativa S.Pellegrino intende offrire e mostrare al mondo la migliore espressione di Made in Italy, quella che tutti amano e apprezzano.
Il progetto prevede ‐ da quest'anno e per il futuro ‐ il coinvolgimento, accanto a S.Pellegrino, di un altro grande marchio italiano leader nel proprio settore (dalla moda al design, dalla pittura alla musica...) e di eccellenza internazionalmente riconosciuta. A questo marchio o firma sarà affidata la storica bottiglia S.Pellegrino, oggi protagonista e ambasciatrice del Live in Italian sulle migliori tavole di tutto il mondo, per interpretarla e dare vita ad un'Edizione speciale che verrà distribuita nei migliori ristoranti in Italia e all'estero per un periodo di circa tre mesi.
A sostegno dell'iniziativa i due marchi lavoreranno congiuntamente ad un piano di comunicazione che include la creazione di una bottiglia da collezione a tiratura limitata, una campagna PR e road show internazionali.

title: 香港十大消失連鎖食店 Top 10 Hong Kong Classic Vanished Restaurants
description:
香港出現過唔少連鎖餐廳、酒樓或快餐店，陪伴著唔少人度過愉快時光。幾十年來，各式各樣嘅快餐店陪住香港人成長。有啲仍然風光，有啲只能回味。你腦海閃起嘅有冇哈迪斯、陽光一代同出奇老鼠？香港飲食業一直競爭激烈，好多都風光一時。選出呢十大，你哋又食過未？ Text: Wong Ki

10) 烤雞大王
喺KFC未壟斷快餐雞市場嘅80、90年代，香港出現本土專攻食雞嘅快餐店－烤雞大王，分店多數位於日資百貨公司food court。戴上膠手套手撕全隻燒雞，配埋粟米真係非常美味，令到另一同業大家樂出「燒春雞」系列打對台，可見點樣風靡一時，可惜只得一時。港產片《最佳損友》，劉華同陳百祥等人食雞食到津津有味，就係喺烤雞大王取景。

9) 農場餐廳
農家意粉前身就係農場餐廳。農場餐廳係香港90年代興起嘅連鎖餐廳，主打簡樸西餐，以抵食、真材實料見稱，高峰時全港分店近50間，只可惜老闆陳興濤喺97年金融風暴破產，全線執笠。2000年代尾東山再起，開「農家意粉」，有分店，結果蝕成千萬，今年年初最後一家都執埋。

8) 金龍船
2000年左右狂擴充餅店同酒樓，應該係為咗上市。賣嘅點心同西餅好靚，價錢當然亦有份量，又賣過廣告，主角係蕭正楠。2003年受沙士影響，生意差，最終捱唔住全線結業。

7) 東東雲吞麵
相信好多人大多透過電視廣告認識呢家粉麵連鎖店，「東東麵，非常麵」，又唱歌又急口令，宣傳包裝真係一流，八十年代時期，東東雲吞麵快餐店業務發展蓬勃，可惜食物品質參差不穩，選擇不多，00年後陸續結業。現在喺超市間中見到東東急凍雲吞同水餃。

6) Wendy's
90年代香港出現好多美式連鎖快餐，除咗Hardee's仲有Wendy's，俾香港人多個選擇。Wendy's是第三大漢堡包快餐連鎖店，80年代以「得意妹」為名登陸香港，惜三年後敗走。91年以「雲狄斯」之名再進軍香港，高峯期擁有11間分店，可惜宣傳策略始終不及麥當勞，未受小朋友歡迎，06年撤出香港。

5) 陽光一代
當年在玻璃櫥窗前看着師傅轉動手上的薄餅，是80後小學生每天放學後最愛的節目。最記得當時其中一間舖喺沙田新城市廣場，現在近GAP服裝店果個位置，門面有塊大櫥窗睇到師傅轉Pizza，成為當時小朋友一大娛樂。屬於香港公司嘅陽光一代，由開餐廳轉型其他界別求存，例如中小學飯盒，仲有「波仔飯」，越做越大。

4) 馬里奧餐廳
專攻意大利口味食品嘅香港連鎖餐廳，裡面有咩食冇咩印象，但最記得係首電視廣告歌，有個疑似著名意大利男高音盧奇亞諾·巴伐洛堤唱歌介紹餐廳嘢食，之後有個細路大叫Mamma Mia。仲有《國產凌凌漆》銅鑼灣皇室堡槍戰一幕背後嘅餐廳門面。呢間屬於大快活集團嘅餐廳，似乎不敵同業Pizza Hut，最終逃唔過易手倒閉命運。

3) 雅香園
70年代的香港人，對24小時營業的雅香園不會感到陌生。
對呢間港式快餐店有印象嘅多數都係70後。專賣中式粉麵，80年代風行一時，希望可以殺出條中式快餐血路，當時仲推出24小時營業，創了香港飲食先河，聽前輩說，餐廳不衛生，係執笠其中一個原因。
P.S. 雅香園曾賣過電視廣告，主角係Beyond黃家強
 
2) 出奇老鼠
呢家80年代風行嘅美資連鎖餐廳好多人都記得，食Pizza又有室內遊樂場，咁樣crossover法真係好獨特，亦令小朋友樂而忘返，但最終都撤資返去美國，歡樂天地取而代之。

1) 哈迪斯
美國連鎖式快餐，90年代進軍香港。80後對於哈迪斯有深厚感情，除了炸薯圈，蘑菇飯最深入民心，可惜不敵肯德基及麥當勞，最終 2006年全線結業，原因係租金同經營權嘅問題。事實止Hardee's風光時期香港、台灣、新加坡、日本等都有分店，而家縮到只可以喺美國及中東地區先食到。

title: 'BFF (Best Friends Forever)' Official Full Trailer | Star Cinema
description:
Honey (Sharon Cuneta), is a conservative homemaker in a twenty-year marriage to Tim (John Estrada). Honey finds a pair of sexy lingerie in her husband’s possession, a confirmation that Tim has been seeing another woman. Not wanting to lose her family of four children, she does not confront her husband about it and instead decides to gather more facts. She enrolls in a gym to make herself physically appealing. There, she meets the liberal and fun-loving fitness instructor, Frances (AiAi delas Alas), who helps her with her problems both inside and outside the gym. Their contrasting personalities give them different perspectives on relationships and how to raise their kids. They become the best of friends. That is, until Honey learns that Frances is Tim’s other woman. Honey finds herself torn between saving her marriage and keeping a unique friendship. She tries to steer Frances away from Tim, but the clueless Frances does not allow this to happen. Unwittingly, Honey uses Frances’ habits and attitudes on Tim, and it strengthens their marriage. Their family gets happier while Frances begins to feel Tim distancing from her. When Frances learns that she is a mistress, she breaks up with Tim. Honey is once again caught between taking care of her heartbroken friend and keeping the mistress away from her family’s life. But what if Frances learns that Honey is Tim’s legal wife? Will this signal the end of their friendship?

title: Live with emotions better than money
description:
Never allow yourself to be a slave to finances.

An obsessive view of money can foster unhealthy responses like greed and dishonesty. This can be true whether a person has a lot or a little. When money has that kind of power in a person's life, they become its slave.

When we view money as just a tool, and don't allow ourselves to get emotionally attached to it, we are in control. Remember, it's just printed paper with no intrinsic value whatsoever. You, on the other hand, are extremely valuable. The more you actively share your unique value with the world, the greater your sense of self-worth will become.

title: شئ يحير تتحرك بدون عجلات وتطير بلا أجنحة
description:
عرضت شركة فولكس فاغن (الصين) نموذجا لسيارة مصممة على شكل البيضة
 وتتحرك فوق الطريق دون عجلات وتحلق في الهواء دون أجنحة. فوق شبكة طرق كهرومغناطيسية بارتفاع قدم أو قدمين.
كما أن قائد السيارة يستطيع أن يتحكم في حركتها من خلال مفتاح تحكم بجانبه، 
وقدرة السيارة على التوقف فجأة في حال اقترب أي جسم منها لتجنب وقوع حوادث التصادم.

وعرضت الشركة هذا النموذج في إطار مشروع أطلق في الصين العام الماضي تحت عنوان "السيارات الشعبية"
ويمكن لقائد السيارة أيضا التحكم في تغيير لونها الخارجي من خلال نوع الموسيقى التي سيستمع إليها.

فبعدما فاجأتنا اليابان بالقطار الطلقة الذى يستخدم تقنية الرفع المغناطيسي أي يسبح على القضبان فلا يسبب احتكاكا مع القضبان وسرعته تبلغ 580 كلم/ساعة وهو أسرع قطار في العالم لايستخدم عجلات ويسير بطريقة التنافر المغناطيسى أصبحنا مهيئين لأى مفاجأت جديدة فى نفس هذا المجال العلمى الجديد علم الأنسان مالم يعلم

شكراً للمشاهدة ▭▭▭▭ ... يشرفنى ويسعدنى إشتراككم فى القناة ليصلكم كل جديد غرائب وعجائب المقاطع النادرة

title: NUNCA LE DIGAS NO AL PANDA SUBT. ESPAÑOL
Werbung aus der Flimmerkiste (Trailer)
description:
Ein amüsanter Streifzug durch die Wunderwelt der frühen Fernsehwerbung: Die gute Rama ist wieder da und Bauknecht weiß, was Frauen wünschen. Mecki, Sarotti-Mohr und Bärenmarke-Bär toben in drolligen Trickfilmen über die Mattscheibe. Auch die ersten Fernsehstars preisen Produkte im Pantoffelkino an. Ein witziger Streifzug durch die Wunderwelt der frühen Fernsehwerbung mit flotten Seitenblicken auf die bunte Kino-Werbung!
In den 60er Jahren weht den Deutschen der Duft der großen weiten Welt um die Nase; Neckermann macht´s möglich und der weiße Wirbelwind bläst die Wohnungen blitzblank. Klementine klempnert an Waschmaschinen herum und Afri-Cola entfacht den Flower-power-Rausch. Eine Begegnung der kuriosen Art mit alten Bekannten und vertrauten Tönen: "Mutti, Mutti, er hat überhaupt nicht gebohrt!"

title: Intervalo Comercial da Rede Globo - 08/02/1988 - 3ª Parte
description:
Acessem meu blog ÊHMB De Olho Na TV: https://ehmbdeolhonatv.blogspot.com.br/
Os videos dos canais Danilo Rodrigues e Pedro Janov contém programas completos com os intervalos comerciais, porém esses intervalos não são postados separadamente como costuma fazer o canal do Dilermando Dias. Em conseqüência disso, muita gente deixa de ver uma série de preciosidades da TV brasileira e muita coisa legal acaba sendo desperdiçada. Por essa razão estou fazendo a "Operação Mortadela", fatiando os intervalos comerciais dos programas na íntegra postados pelo Danilo (espero que ele não fique bravo comigo), até porque existem pessoas que não tem tanta paciência em assistir videos de longa duração aqui no YT. Confira agora uma série de três videos com os intervalos comerciais exibidos pela Rede Globo em 8 de fevereiro de 1988 entre a "Sessão Comédia" e um capítulo da novela das seis "Bambolê". Imagens retiradas de um vídeo postado por Fred Danelon, a quem eu expresso meus agradecimentos. Confira o link do canal dele para conferir outras pérolas da TV: www.youtube.com/user/93Fr1

- Là dụng cụ chế biến thực phẩm vô cùng tuyệt vời cho tất cả mọi người mọi nhà, chỉ một chiếc máy Magic Bullet là có thể thay thế cho các loại máy như xay sinh tố, ép trài cây, xay thịt, xay cá, xay cà phê, đánh kem, đánh trứng, nhào bột, xay/băm nhuyễn các loại gia vị thảo mộc, .....
- Máy có hai lưỡi dao phù hợp chế biến tất cả các loại thực phẩm
- Kèm theo máy có sách hướng dẩn công thức pha chế các loại rượi, cocktail, café, nước ép, sinh tố và các món ăn mà chỉ tím thấy ở các nhà hàng sang trọng mới có
CÁCH SỬ DỤNG. 
- Rất đơn giản: Chỉ cần cho các nguyên liệu, thực phẩm vào trong các phụ kiện phù hợp (Cốc, Ca, Bình, Bộ ép...) cùng với lưỡi dao thích hợp và đặt lên đế động cơ rồi ấn nhẹ trong vài giây là bạn thực hiện xong món ăn bạn ưa thích.
- Máy sử dụng hộp inox, thiết kế và kết cấu giá dao chắc chắn. Bàn cốc được phân biệt kiểu mới, khiến cho máy sử dụng an toàn, thuận tiện vệ sinh máy.
- Máy còn có cốc xay thịt dung lượng lớn, vừa dùng để xay thịt, vừa dùng để xay hoa quả rất hữu dụng.
Giữa tiết trời mùa hè nóng nực, hấp dẫn làm sao khi cầm trên tay 1 ly hoa quả nghiền sữa chua mát lạnh. Cơ thể bạn sẽ được thanh nhiệt giải độc thật nhanh chóng. Đặc biệt hơn, nếu bạn muốn trổ tài nấu những món ăn kiểu Tây mới lạ như spaghetti, khoai tây nghiền sốt thịt bò...  máy xay đa năng Magic Buller sẽ là trợ thủ đắc lực của bạn.
Thay vì phải mua máy ép, máy xay sinh tố, máy xay thịt..., chỉ với chiếc máy xay đa năng, tất cả nhu cầu "xay" của gia đình đều được đáp ứng.
Máy xay đa năng được tích hợp nhiều tính năng chỉ trong một thiết bị duy nhất. Mỗi khi có nhu cầu xay loại thực phẩm nào, người dùng chỉ cần lắp chiếc cối tương ứng lên thân máy, nhấn nút. Thế là xong!
Còn gì tuyệt vời hơn, khi sau những giờ làm việc mệt nhọc, về nhà, chỉ cần vài phút thao tác, bạn đã có một ly nước ép trái cây ngon lành hoặc chỉ cần thêm vài phút nữa, bạn cũng sẽ có vài ly sinh tố ngon tuyệt dành cho người thân.

title: Los chicos están bien (The kids are all right) EMON
description: Nic (Annette Benning) y Jules (Julianne Moore) tienen dos hijos, Joni (Mia Wasikowska) y Laser (Josh Hutcherson), que nacieron por inseminación artificial. Joni está en plena adolescencia, a punto de graduarse en la secundaria y pasa por los típicos problemas de esa edad...el alcohol y las ganas de ser popular. De todas formas, si algo le preocupa a ella y a su hermano es conocer a su padre biológico y que donó su esperma (Mark Ruffalo). Por azares del destino, lo encuentran y lo integran en el núcleo familiar. Sin embargo, sus madres no están de acuerdo con ello, lo que irá provocando situaciones de lo más confusas.

description:
Microdermabrasion is a quick and convenient procedure that has become very popular with patients showing the early signs of aging, sun exposure and other facial imperfections.

Microdermabrasion is a closed vacuum system delivering aluminum oxide crystals to the skin. This process exfoliates the thickened epidermis then vacuums away the crystals and skin debris revealing healthier skin. Microdermabrasion results are best when combined with the ALC skin care regimen, and is safe for all skin types.

title: 99 Years of 234. Shot and Directed by Mark Toia
description:
This was a great job to be apart of. I turned it down 4 times, I pushed my schedule out over 4 months and the client still waited for me. It was a job I did not really want to do because I did not think it could be done properly in Jakarta. Also working for big global companies with many voices, and having two AD agencies at the same time on set... I really doubted that it was possible to do a good job. But mid way through pre production with PLUSH PICTURES in Jakarta, i quickly realized that the project was turning into something grand. I had a vision, but did not think Jakarta had the film experience to pull it off. I was gladly mistaken. All the crew and especially the art director WAIKI really bought there "A" game to the table. Everyone could see this turning into something big... everyone started to get behind it... The client and agency were letting me do my thing and did not get in the way at all. We ended up with a great TV Commercial that everyone is proud of. My thanks goes out to all involved. Great work guys... Jakarta's film industry just stepped up to international levels.
I shoot around the world alot, and am spoiled with gear and choice... I was really impressed with the effort everyone put in. Great job Jakarta, great job. !

title: ¿Quien Engaño A Roger Rabbit? Trailer 1988
description:
Siguenos en: http://www.facebook.com/pages/Retro-80s-y-90s/202173183258399.
https://www.youtube.com/user/retro80sy90s

¿Quién engañó a Roger Rabbit? es una película estadounidense de 1988, dirigida por Robert Zemeckis y protagonizada por Bob Hoskins. Producida por Touchstone y Amblin Entertainment, la película combina a personajes reales con dibujos animados y para ello se invirtieron 70 millones de dólares. Es una de las más caras de la historia, pero sus ingresos fueron 150 millones de dólares en taquilla. Además, fue uno de los últimos trabajos de los actores de voz Mel Blanc y Mae Questel.

Compilation of vintage hot dog clips: little boy eats hot dog (Little Rascals / Our Gang). Hot dog sprays girl in the face. New York mayor Fiorello LaGuardia eats hot dogs with group of boys. Man eats hot dog at bar, drops hot dog into glass of wine. Fat man eats hot dog at Dodgers Stadium in Brooklyn. Boys eat hot dogs at fair. Teenage couple eats hot dogs on date at school dance. People eat hot dogs on boardwalk. Woman stuffs her face. Raymond Hitchcock gives hot dog to camel. Jack Benny at carnival with kids. Benny orders hot dogs for kids. Benny jokes around with hot dog seller. Man at hot dog cart in New York City. Hot dogs on display in deli. Man eats hot dogs on boardwalk. Babe Ruth eats hot dogs with kids. Hot dogs in wheelbarrow at outdoor bbq. College kids eat hot dogs. Man cooks hot dogs over fire at campsite. Hot dogs cooked on rotating grill. Hot dogs cooked on outdoor grill. Boy Scouts eat hot dogs. Kids eat hot dogs at outdoor picnic. Man makes hot dogs in factory. Frankfurters linked. Frankfurters packaged on conveyor belt. Animated lion reaches for hot dog from cart. Mouse puts lion's tail in hot dog bun. Lion screams in pain, looks at crooked tail. Little girls eat hot dogs. Asian woman eats hot dog on street. Man eats hot dog in park. CU woman eats hot dog at baseball game. Hot dogs on grill. Teens eat hot dogs at party. Men eat hot dogs at outdoor cart. CU Hot dog slathered in mustard. Hippie duo sing in front of hot dog stand. Hot dog factory. Mustard, relish, and sauerkraut onto hot dog. Hot dog buns in factory. 

For licensing and rates, please visit: http://www.filmarchivesonline.com

title: John Malkovich - 1991 The Object Of Beauty Trailer
description: Jake (John Malkovich) and Tina (Andie MacDowell) are a glamorous American couple camping out in a suite in a swank London hotel. They're unable to settle their account, which when the movie begins stands at about six thousand pounds, because Jake, a speculator, has blown all his money on a bad investment. Jake and Tina are unmarried and have no permanent address; they're charming, attractive drifters, getting by on style. In a sense, they're throwbacks to the sophisticated and slightly disreputable couples who floated airily through thirties romantic comedies: no-strings types who stick together for the best shallow reasons-for sex and laughs and the shared kick of living the high life without having to work too hard. The picture, written and directed by Michael Lindsay-Hogg, is conceived as high-style fluff, but it never delivers quite as much irresponsible fun as it promises. It's like a Lubitsch movie without the speed and the grace and the blissful inconsequentiality. Malkovich, however, is as unaccountably magnetic here as he was in "Dangerous Liaisons." His performance is a postmodern mutation of thirties style, an ungodly hybrid of William Powell and Boris Karloff, and it's sensationally funny. This is as original a piece of acting as you'll ever see in a romantic comedy. The supporting players are an unusually lively group: Lolita Davidovich, Peter Riegert, Joss Ackland, and Bill Paterson.

title: Five good reasons why - 90s game commercials are totally rad
description:
Way before video games became the multi-billion dollar industry it is today, we relied on television ads to see which games looked fun enough to warrant investing our hard-earned money in. Here are five good reasons why old video game commercials are totally rad!

5. You could rap

It's The Legend Of Zelda and it's really rad! Rapping in the 80s wasn't considered bad. It might sound completely ridiculous now. But back then they got away with it somehow.

4. Bit wars

From the time that the Genesis first challenged the NES, the "bit wars" were a huge part of console marketing. The "bitness" of your system was it measure of merit, and people fiercely argued which system had more of a right to be called "8-Bit" or "16-Bit". We love how old video game commercials hyped consoles based on bits as if it's the most important thing in the world.  

3. They got you hyped

We all know the Power Glove is a piece of shit now but just look at how it's being presented in this commercial. The smoke machine, lighting effects and computer voice makes it seem like the most awesome thing in the world. It might be false advertising but nothing gets you hyped like a good old school video game commercial. 

2. You could insult the competition

Gamers loved it when Sony called out Microsoft over the DRM bullshit on the Xbox One. But that was nothing compared to the full out war Sega waged against Nintendo in the 80s and 90s. The power gloves really came off in these commercials… Schoolyards were turned into battlefields of the most ruthless type thanks to these ads. Good times … good times. 

1. The ads were funny

We love watching old video game commercials because they are funny. It's hard not to laugh at the completely bizarre Atari ads… The Sonic the Hedgehog 2 infomercial … or cute Nintendo characters beating the crap out of each other in this Smash Bros ad. We also love how a fake laundry commercial turns into an ad for the N64 game Battle Tanx. And the Japanese Sega commercials in which a badass by the name of Segata Sanshiro beats you up unless you buy a Saturn. Please don't hurt us mr. Sanshiro were promise we'll buy your Sega Saturn!

title: Mattel Electronics Intellivision PlayCable Adapter commercials - unedited (feat. Mickey Mantle)
description:
All 5 commercials for Mattel Electronics PlayCable Adapter for their Intellivision video game system, featuring baseball legend Mickey Mantle.  These were first aired in 1982.  This is a unedited copy of the master tape.  A copy of these were provided to Keith Robinson of Intellivision Productions.

The PlayCable system, introduced in 1981, allowed local cable-TV system operators to send Intellivision games over the wire alongside the normal TV signal. Subscribers to the service could then use a special converter—the PlayCable Adapter—to download the games to play on their Intellivision game consoles.

The PlayCable Adapter connected to the Intellivision via the game-cartridge slot on the side, just like any other game. Once connected, switching on the Intellivision would bring up an on-screen menu showing which games were available to play. (Typically, several different titles would be available at any given time, with the available selection changing from month to month.) The system was not truly interactive, though; the program code for all of the available games was simply broadcast over the cable connection constantly, and whenever the user selected a game the Adapter would simply wait until that particular bit of code came past, grab it off the line, and load it into its internal memory. The Intellivision would then read the Adapter's memory as if it were a normal ROM cartridge.

Unfortunately, the PlayCable Adapters only had 4K of RAM in them. While this was sufficient for most Intellivision game titles in 1981, it wasn't long before more complex games started appearing on 8K and 16K cartridges, which the PlayCable could not support. This made the system increasingly less attractive to customers, since it was limited to supporting only the older game titles, and the system was eventually discontinued in 1983.

Since the PlayCable adapters were rented from the local cable-TV company, rather than purchased outright, they all had to be returned when the system was discontinued. Thus, very few of them are known to still exist, making them an extremely rare item for Intellivision collectors.

For more information, check out INTV Funhouse's website: http://www.intvfunhouse.com/hardware/playcable/

title: Toy Story 3
description:
http://ow.ly/3d49A Toy Story 3 is a 2010 American 3D computer-animated film. It is the third and currently final film in the Toy Story series.[4] The film was produced by Pixar Animation Studios and released by Walt Disney Pictures. Lee Unkrich, who edited the previous films, and co-directed the second, took over as director. In his place, Ken Schretzmann is the editor. Toy Story 3 was also the first of only two films to be released theatrically with 7.1 surround sound, the second being Step Up 3D.

Tom Hanks, Tim Allen, Joan Cusack, Don Rickles, Estelle Harris, John Ratzenberger, Wallace Shawn, Jeff Pidgeon, Jodi Benson, R. Lee Ermey, John Morris, and Laurie Metcalf all reprised their voice-over roles from the previous films. Jim Varney, who played Slinky Dog in the first two films, and Joe Ranft, who portrayed Wheezy and Lenny, both died before production began on the third film. The role of Slinky was taken over by Blake Clark, while Ranft's characters and various others were written out of the story (Wheezy, Etch, and Bo Peep, for example, are mentioned in the beginning as having been sold). New characters include voice-overs by Ned Beatty, Timothy Dalton, Bonnie Hunt, Whoopi Goldberg, Jeff Garlin, and Michael Keaton.

Toy Story 3 was released worldwide from June through October in Disney Digital 3-D, RealD and IMAX 3D. The feature broke the record of Shrek the Third as the biggest opening day North American gross for an animated film unadjusted for inflation and a big opening with an unadjusted gross of $110,307,189.[5][6] It is also the highest-grossing opening weekend for a Pixar film, as well as the highest-grossing opening weekend for a film to have opened in the month of June.

The film is currently the highest-grossing film of 2010 in the United States and Canada, and the highest-grossing film of 2010 worldwide. In July, it surpassed Finding Nemo to become Pixar's highest ever grossing film at the North American box office. In early August, the film became Pixar's highest-grossing film worldwide and surpassed Shrek 2 as the highest-grossing animated film of all-time worldwide; in late August, Toy Story 3 became the first ever Pixar film and animated film in history to make over $1 billion worldwide. It is currently the 5th highest-grossing film worldwide of all time

title: The History of Herb
description:
This video is the history, usage, and contexts to which the slang term 'herb' may be used. A little video that myself and a few other herbs put together.
The word 'Herb' was once thought to be the shortened version of the male name Herbert. Well back in the 1980's Burger King started an advertising campaign around that name, but during the early to mid 1990's this name adapted itself into slang.

I have been saying it since I was a nino, due in part to my brother Nick who introduced me to the term in the mid 1990's.

All you herbs out there, you don't know who you are, but we do.

Credits:
Kyle Diorio_NJ_USA (editing, concept, script)
Scott Guadagnino_PA_USA (concept)
Joey Wagner_San Fran_CA (content editor)

Laserneg sono un progetto musicale che nasce nel 2010 dall'unione del deejay Dario Viale e della cantante e conduttrice televisiva Katia Nicotra.

Il primo singolo chiamato "Tiru tiratta" uscito il 28 maggio scorso ha avuto un buon successo, soprattutto all'estero dove i Laserneg sono stati inseriti all'interno di una ventina di compilations dance, pop dance e italo-dance del settore.

From Sessions- the 70s were way over by this time, but mail-order compilation albums lasted into the 80s.  You gotta love the people on the cover of this- they look like rejects from a soft-core porn video.  I have this but one of the records is missing- they all come in one thick sleeve, not 4 as shown here.

CDs were out by this time, but I never saw any mail-order albums have them available for a couple more years.  They'd finally given up on 8-tracks by now though.  TV was stereo by now too but very few commercials were produced in stereo til the 90s.

title: Communication is Power: Mass Media & Mass Persuasion Screener
description:
Screener for Communication is Power: Mass Media & Mass Persuasion distributed by Contemporary Arts Media http://www.artfilms.com.au


Advertising, violence and a growing influence of electronic media in politics. Advertising, in one form or another, will appear in any society where there is trade or competition. Understanding the techniques of advertising can give insight into many other forms of mass persuasion. For the methods used to sell us products are also used to sell us candidates, ideas, even life styles. Advertising seldom tells the whole truth. It often employs exaggeration, or "puffery" to impress customers. Or else it extols the vertues of a products, while neglecting to mention its faults (as used in car ads).

The impact of advertising on our society is undeniable. People often criticize its half-truths and bad taste, and deplore the way it persuades consumers to buy what they don't relly need. On the other hand, advertisin is often the only way for a company or product to overcome natural suspicions of the new and unknown. Understanding the techniques of advertising may prove to be the consumer's best protection against being manipulated. 60 mins.

Đôi lúc bạn cảm thấy buồn chán vì cuộc sống xung quanh mình, mỗi quan hệ giữa người với người ngày càng trở nên lạnh nhạt hơn, họ trở nên thờ ơ trước những việc xảy ra hàng ngày ngay trước mắt mình mà chẳng cận bận tâm, chỉ cần việc đó không đụng chạm gì tới quyền lợi của mình là được. Nhưng ở trong một xã hội như vậy, vẫn còn rất nhiều người tốt mà bạn vô tâm vẫn không để ý tới, họ làm những việc nhỏ nhặt âm thầm để giúp đỡ mọi người, không ngại mệt mỏi, và đôi khi chịu phần thiệt cho bản thân. Xem đoạn clip xong có thể làm bạn nghĩ lại về cuộc sống này và hãy sống một cách tích cực hơn nhé.

title: Yummy for your Tummy: Westcountry Adverts, 1998
description:
The third commercial break in Predator 2 starts with a bit of U-rated soft-focus pornography featuring Andy Williams (not participating in the pornography, fortunately) and advertising the Peugeot 306.

Next is an advert for a failure on the part of Camelot, the kind of thing that lost them the licence a couple of years later (they got it back when the Government remembered how good they were at stuffing envelopes full of banknotes). TV Dreams was intended to be interactive - not only could you win the chance to appear on the TV show fronted by Anthea Turner the following month, but you could also buy a scratchcard and play along at home! Except it was so half-arsed no-one bothered. And the show didn't work, mainly because the winning audience members couldn't actually do anything because it would violate the concept of a lottery. And the TV play game was hosted by a CGI animated-on-the-fly barfly woman with the voice of Kate Robbins, superimposed on the live footage of the draw, which was a terrible idea, and demonstrated such by promptly disintegrating into a bunch of lines, leaving Kate to desperately improvise her way out of it live on TV. And Camelot ended up getting rapped on the knuckles for encouraging gambling. So yeah, well done.

Then, incomprehensible then-Newcastle manager Kenny Dalglish explains why the Bristol and West is so bloody great. There were a lot of these, all with the same basic script and the same pre-Channel 4 whipping-round-to-reveal-the-logo ending. John Peel was on another one. He only advertised things he actually used, so presumably he had an account at the B&W and ate Trios.

Next is Jif, which apparently consists of several little men who run around your kitchen kicking germs to death. And whistling.

Apparently it's late at night by now, because here's one of those faintly nightmarish adverts for a singles network chatline thing that I had trouble believing anyone ever used. These things were never even close to specific as to what they consisted of, but then they didn't really need to be.

If that was faintly nightmarish, the next one is an actual nightmare, a condensed version of one set in some kind of netherworld that apparently exists in the mind of a Care Bear with a fever. The voice of Joe Pasquale completely fails to explain what's going on. Precisely what this is doing being advertised in the middle of Predator 2 is anyone's guess.

Then that Lynx Apollo thing is back, and there's a reprise of that terrible Lottery idea, and then a glimpse at the late Kevin Peter Hall.

title: Un Buen Año Russell Crowe Trailer en Español A good year Movie
description:
SUSCRÍBETE: http://goo.gl/JFCEuh

SÍGUEME EN:
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/pages/Experiumes/387544691317701
Twitter: https://twitter.com/experiummarkets
Instagram: http://instagram.com/experiummarkets
Pinterest: http://www.pinterest.com/experiummarkets/

http://www.experium.es

Engreído y seguro de sí mismo, cabezota y bien parecido, Max Skinner es un exitoso financiero especializado en comercio de bonos. Tiburón financiero a orillas del Támesis, Max devora a sus competidores en un intento de hacerse con el mercado europeo. Su última conquista ha dado como rédito un beneficio neto de siete cifras, con gran pesadumbre para sus rivales vestidos primorosamente en Saville Row. El triunfo de Max está en perfecta consonancia con su filosofía: ganar no lo es todo, ¡es lo único que hay!

Muy poco después, Max recibe una carta desde Francia que contiene malas noticias: su viejo tío Henry ha fallecido. Max, el pariente más cercano de Henry, es el único beneficiario de su herencia: una finca que incluye una casa de campo en Provenza y un viñedo, La Siroque, en la que Henry ha estado cultivando vides durante más de treinta años.

Max viaja hasta la casa de campo en la que pasó las vacaciones de los veranos de su infancia con su excéntrico tío, a quien no ha visto o escrito en años. Mientas Max atiende a los asuntos legales de su herencia, se encuentra suspendido de empleo y sueldo por su firma, pendiente de una investigación por una más que cuestionable transacción de bonos.

Con su futuro en Londres en el aire, Max a regañadientes empieza a habitar en la casa de campo. Se reúne con el veterano cuidador de las viñas de la finca, Francis Duflot (que todavía se encarga de las vides después de tres décadas), a quien Max recuerda de sus visitas infantiles. La exuberante mujer de Duflot, Ludivine, la casera de la finca, recibe a Max de forma muy cálida.

Max no tiene muy claro si sabrá hacerse a la vida en el sur de Francia ni si sentirá cómodo allí. Llama a su mejor amigo, el agente inmobiliario de Londres Charlie Willis, para preguntarle qué papel puede desempeñar hacer un pequeño viñedo y una finca como La Siroque en el mercado actual. Charlie le advierte a Max que las pequeñas bodegas con un buen producto pueden generar varios millones de dólares, pues el vino de boutique, elaborado en pequeñas cantidades, es lo más en las tiendas de vino. Es dinero en el banco para Max si al final pierde su trabajo.

Mientras Max recupera con cariño los recuerdos de sus veranos pasados (junto a un hombre cuya sabiduría y filosofía ayudaron a Max a dirigir su exitosa carrera), aun contemplando un oscuro futuro, surge un contratiempo con la repentina llegada de una decidida chica veinteañera de California llamada Christie Roberts. Christie, natural del Valle de Napa, alega ser la hija ilegítima de su fallecido tío. La revelación, de ser cierta, le convierte en prima de Max y, de acuerdo con la ley francesa, en la beneficiaria de La Siroque.

Sospechando que Christie quizás sea una impostora, Max indaga en su pasado haciéndole mil y una preguntas, mientras anda a la greña con ella por el destino de la bodega, cuyo vino está a la altura del peor vinagre que se pudiera imaginar. Max, que ha probado el terrible vin de pays (vino de mesa) de La Siroque, también encuentra algunas botellas en la bodega del tío Henry con el nombre de Le Coin Perdu ('El Rincón Perdido'). Este misterioso y legendario vino de garaje se ha vendido a miles de dólares en el mercado negro durante años, según Fanny Chanel, la atractiva propietaria de un café local por la que Max se ha sentido atraído.

¿De dónde sale ese vino y por qué insiste tanto Duflot en seguir en La Siroque sea cual sea el destino del viñedo? Y, ¿qué decir de algunas vides muy poco comunes descubiertas en la finca por Christie, que el brusco vinatero argumenta que son un experimento y un afamado enólogo ha estimado de escaso valor?

Los recuerdos de Max y el transcurso del tiempo sacan a relucir emociones y sentimientos que pensaba ya perdidos, y le permiten tener en nueva estima la filosofía de vida de su fallecido tío Henry y de la vida en la Provenza: "No hay ningún otro lugar en el mundo en el que uno pueda estar atareado haciendo tan poca cosa ¡y disfrutándolo tanto!"

title: Patriotic ads from Liberty Weekend - July 3-4, 1986
description:
Selected commercials from ABCs Liberty Weekend coverage July 3-4, 1986. All explicitly reference the Statue of Liberty's centennial, or involve lots of flags, commemorative coins, and other July Fourth symbolism. - 7-Eleven - "The New American" (I feel a little wrong being amused by the fact that they're acknowledging that there's a little truth to the stereotype) 
- The Prudential (The company "salutes the Statue on her 100th birthday" and says it insured immigrants' dream when no one else would.
- Stroh Brewery Co. - "As the Statue lives on, so does the dream." (Sweeping aerial shots of the Statue of LIberty at sunset, set to John Lennon's "Imagine.")
- Liberty Coins from the U.S. Treasury (coin slowly rises to "America, the Beautiful")
- Van Heusen (From the "For a Man to Wear. And a Woman to Borrow." campaign. Includes a little girl celebrating "a very special birthday" by wearing her dad's very special shirt.)
- Texaco (A video montage set to a country-tinged version of "Stand Up for the Flag of America" shows "how the men and women of Texaco feel about our flag and freedom" - and is apparently based on an earlier ad. The voiceover is longtime pitchman Bob Hope, honored with the Medal of Liberty during the weekend's festivities)
- Wrangler (Shots of the Statue of Liberty are interspersed with footage of "legend in jeans" Willie Nelson performing "City of New Orleans," aka "Good mornin', America, how are ya?"
- Liberty Coins (A slightly more interesting version of the previous ad - but it can't hold a candle to the next one.)
- Plymouth - "The Pride is Back." (Almost wasn't included, but the statue shot plus oodles of flags pushed it over the top.)
- Liberty Coins (In 2050, we'll all have mini-planes and fly right up to the Statue of Liberty!)

title: Una historia animada de la Coca-Cola
description: Esto es un excelente resumen de la historia de The Coca-Cola Company. La historia del video en sí también es interesante. Fue producido originalmente en Rusia como parte de un especial de televisión de 30 minutos llamado "En busca de la fórmula secreta." Dicha emisión fue creada con el fin de presentar la Coca-Cola al mercado ruso. El video nos gustó tanto que lo mandé a traducir al inglés y se utilizó como una introducción al Mundo de Coca-Cola en Atlanta. Esta es la versión en español. Aunque el video fue concebido hace más de 10 años, el estilo de animación así como la historia siguen siendo pertinentes.

title: Because Enough is Enough Music Video
description:

It is the theme song for the Queensland transport's campaign to reduce road deaths caused by car accidents through speeding, drinking, drugs. etc. This video is not the official music video for this song, this is simply just something that I decided to put together the other afternoon as I was listening to this song. Unfortunately it is unclear who wrote this song, but it does belong to the Queensland Transport Department and is available at www.queenslandtransport.gov.au . title: Coletânea de Vinhetas da TV Itacolomi - Anos 50/60
description: Saindo do eixo Rio-São Paulo, faço agora uma homenagem aos nosso compadres mineiros. Esta é uma compliação de videos retirados das contas MemoriaPUCTV, BrazilWorldTV e Comte e eis aqui a mais completa coletânea de vinhetas da saudosa TV Itacolomi de Belo Horizonte, a primeira emissora de TV fora do eixo Rio-São Paulo, que entrou no ar em 8 de novembro de 1955 pelos Diários Associados de Assis Chateaubriandt, pertencentes à TV Tupi. Essa emissora permaneceu no ar por quase 25 anos, sua imagem alcançava cerca de 600 municípios mineiros e por muito tempo era líder imbatível de audiência em Minas Gerais, atingindo altos picos de 80%, cujos índices dificilmente (ou raramente) foram igualados na capital mineira. Contando com 300 funcionários, sua programação era composta de peças teatrais, humor, teledramaturgia, jornalismo, programas de auditório e esporte, além de ter sido pioneira nos chamados telecursos matinais. O curioso é que por 10 anos seguidos, sua programação era inteiramente ao vivo e foi somente a partir de 1965 que chegou o primeiro aparelho de video-tape na emissora, quando sua grade foi reformulada com a aquisição de modernos equipamentos para a época. A liderança absoluta de audiência foi sempre ressaltada em suas vinhetas e ostentou tal posição por 17 anos até ser "driblada" pela Rede Globo nos boletins do IBOPE, em 1973. A belíssima trajetória da Itacolomi encerrou-se em 18 de julho de 1980, quando o Ministério das Comunicações, na véspera, declarou extinta sete concessões pertencentes à TV Tupi por dívidas, não-renovação das concessões de TV e má gestão. Os transmissores da emissora mineira foram lacrados às 10h27 daquele mesmo dia, quando imprimia tela a barra padrão de cores, o color-bass, pois havia se despedido no dia anterior (quando foi anunciada a extinção da TV Tupi) emitindo flashes históricos com um resumo de seus quase 25 anos de fundação e ainda responsabilizou o Goveno Federal pelo reaproveitamento de seus 300 funcionários. Sua última imagem era o slide do seu logo com uma abatida mensagem "Até logo", que permaneceu no ar por longas horas até sair do ar. Para quem curte a memória da TV brasileira, apreciem este documento histórico, e em especial para os nossos queridos mineiros, é hora de matar as saudades!

title: Television for doctors, circa 1991 - part 1
description:
Here are some show promos, openings and disclaimer-laden prescription drug ads for the trade aired during educational programming for doctors, taped off cable in November 1991.

Most are from Lifetime Medical Television - a service Lifetime ran from 1983 to 1993, turning "television for women" into "the network for doctors only" every Sunday. A few are from a competing service, American Medical Television, run by the American Medical Association on CNBC.

- "Milestones in Medicine" show opening
- Ad for Seldane-D (a nonsedating antihistamine decongestant for allergy sufferers)
- American Medical Television message on how to get full prescribing information on advertised drugs
- AMT "Practical Medicine" bumper
- Ad for Voltaren (a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug - NSAID - for arthritis) - starring a retired ballerina who apparently gets around, as this showed up several times on the tape.
- Lifetime Medical Television promo - "Where doctors turn ... to learn."
- Ad for Tagamet (a drug for ulcers) - a dutiful son running the family deli talks about the difference Tagamet made for his dad; includes the ironic line "Who's gonna pay $10 for a pound of coffee?"
- Promo for "MedQuiz," a game show in which senior residents from Massachusetts General, Barnes Hospital in St. Louis and Stanford University Hospital are contestants.
- Ad for Vasotec (adjunctive therapy for severe congestive heart failure) - this ad just about breaks my heart.
- Ad for Feldene (NSAID for osteoarthritis and rheumatoid arthritis) - Pop quiz time!
- Promo for "Milestones in Medicine," which I guess was shown on both channels
- LMT prescribing information message
- Opening sequence for "Physicians' Journal Update" for Nov. 3, 1991.
- Promo for "Family Practice Update"

title: 井川遥、CMのあの店で「乾杯！」　「角ハイボール CMのあのお店」オープニングイベント(1)
description:
★エンタメニュースを毎日掲載！「MAiDiGiTV」登録はこちら↓
http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=maidigitv

女優の井川遥さんが10月8日、東京都内で行われた出演するCMのイベントに登場。8日から東京と大阪で期間限定でオープンする店「角ハイボール CMのあのお店」のオープニングイベントで井川さんは、落ち着いた白のシャツにエプロン姿で登場し、角ハイボールで乾杯するシーンもあった。「この雰囲気も手伝って、炭酸が強いからスカッとしますね。やっぱりおいしいです」とコメントし、オープンした店については「ものすごい完成度で、まさに“あのお店”そのものだなと」と感想を語った。

同店は井川さんが出演しているサントリーのテレビCMの舞台となっている店を再現したもので、13日までの期間限定で六本木ヒルズ「大屋根プラザ」と、グランフロント大阪「ナレッジプラザ」の2カ所でオープンする。お店では角ハイボールやからあげなどのフードを販売する。

井川さんは実際に知人などにリクエストされて「（ハイボールを）作ったこともあります」とにっこり。「混ぜすぎないことで香り高く、炭酸の強い発泡した感じが楽しめます」と家庭で作るコツも披露した。

title: What is targeted TV advertising?
description:
Learn about the basics of targeted TV advertising and how it can help viewers, marketers, agencies, and ad sellers.

For more information, please visit visibleworld.com.

Transcript:
• Consumers have different lifestyles, which means the things they buy (and why they buy them) are different. So why do they all see the same TV ads?
• TV advertising used to be pretty straightforward. A single media buy could give you access to a huge part of the population. Unfortunately, things aren't that simple anymore.
• More channels, more devices, more fragmentation -- today's audiences are a lot harder to pin down.
• No surprise then that many marketers are turning to online advertising. Online, it's relatively easy to target specific audiences, tailor ads to make them more relevant and to measure their performance. But when it comes to reach and popularity, television still reigns supreme.
• Wouldn't it be great if you could combine the efficient reach of TV with the effectiveness of highly targeted ads? Well, now you can -- with Visible World's targeted TV advertising.
• Our targeted TV advertising makes the most of the broad, efficient reach of television by enabling you to target different ads to different consumer groups, based on more meaningful criteria than just age and gender. It's all about making your messages more relevant - and effective.
• Complicated? Not with Visible World's award winning technology. We've automated the process of targeting TV ads to make it easy, fast and smart. Up-to-date reporting lets you measure what's going on, so you can fine tune your efforts, even in the middle of the campaign.
• The result? Everyone's happy. Viewers see ads that are relevant to them. And marketers see their ads work harder, with less effort. And that makes TV ads more valuable for everyone.
• Find out what targeted TV advertising can do for you.

title: The Most Effective Advertising May Be When Consumers Least Expect It
description:
In the age of digital video recorders (DVRs) many advertisers have lamented that consumers aren't as influenced by ads because they have the ability to fast forward through or even skip the commercials.

But new research from Duke University's Fuqua School of Business suggests the opposite could be true: Consumers might be more influenced when they aren't focusing on advertisements and their defenses are down.
 
The researchers also found that while watching fast-forwarded ads, consumers are most influenced when they see brands they perceive as very different from each other in a back-to-back ad block.
 
"We feel these findings have important implications for the way advertisers place their promotional messages -- both in traditional television spots, as well as in a variety of brief brand exposure settings," said Fuqua marketing professor Gavan Fitzsimons. "The media landscape is a totally different ballgame than it was even just a few years ago."
 
The research, "Distinctively Different: Exposure to Multiple Brands in Low Elaboration Settings," was just published online in the Journal of Consumer Research.
 
In one study that examined a product-placement setting, 89 undergraduate students were shown photos depicting various combinations of Dove Chocolate, Canada Dry and Mountain Dew.  The research team wanted to understand if Dove Chocolate would "pop" more when it was in a photo with Canada Dry (both brands are perceived to be similar by consumers who tend to feel the brands are sincere) versus in a photo with a can of Mountain Dew (brands that are viewed as very different with Mountain Dew being perceived as more edgy by consumers).

One group of students was encouraged to think carefully about the photos, while the other was distracted from the fact there were brands in the photos because they thought the research was focusing on the emotions of the people in the photographs.
 
Results showed participants were more likely to subsequently choose Dove Chocolate when it was paired with a dissimilar brand, but only when they were not thinking carefully about the products. When they did think carefully about them, participants were more likely to choose a similar brand.
 
"This study shows when a consumer's defenses are down and they aren't thinking about the products they are exposed to, the differences between one brand and another are highlighted, making it really stand out without the consumer realizing it," Fitzsimons said.
 
A second study looked specifically at how consumers react to various brands when fast-forwarding with DVRs. Researchers showed 84 undergraduates clips of a television show with commercials from Mountain Dew, Hummer and Honda Pilot. The research team wanted to see if the students were more likely to choose Mountain Dew if the commercial ran next to Hummer (brands most consumers view as exciting) or Honda Pilot (a very different brand many consumers view as sincere). 
 
Half of the participants watched the commercials at regular speed while the other half watched at 10 times regular speed (a typical pace when fast-forwarding past ads using a DVR). Results showed consumers were more likely to pick Mountain Dew when it was paired with the dissimilar brand, but only when watching the commercials in fast forward.
 
"This experiment reinforced for us that the pairing of dissimilar brands really only works when the consumer isn't thinking about the commercial, but is focused on another task like when to stop fast-forwarding so they don't miss some of the program they're watching, " said co-author Tanya Chartrand, also a marketing professor at the Fuqua School of Business.
 
The research has significant implications for advertisers.
 
"Our findings suggest that the brand personalities many companies have so painstakingly cultivated may be influenced in ways that are difficult to control, namely by the brand personalities of other products in the same advertising block, or in the same visual field," Fitzsimons said. "On the other hand, understanding the interplay of brands and their contexts in a new media environment should help firms better place their messages so their customers are most likely to choose them, and be very happy they did so."
 
Other authors of the study were former Duke Ph.D. students Linyun Yang (now a faculty member at the University of North Carolina-Charlotte), and Keisha Cutright (now a faculty member at the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania).

The final ad break between "The Simpsons Quiz Show" and the penultimate upload from this batch. For a 30 minute show, it sure has a lot of ad breaks. Hmm. Still, what can ya do?

Well I know what I'll do, write THIS down. CONTENTS!:
1) "Sponsered by Pizza Hut" bumper / "The Simpsons on 4" sting
2) UK TV advert for "Eye Toy Play 2" and the Eye Toy for the PlayStation 2 (I had the "Sega Superstars" Eye Toy game myself. The only good game was the House of the Dead one. Which WAS a hell of a lot of fun. But yeah, the Eye Toy was pretty cool. Kinect but without the paranoia. ;D)
3) Daily Mail/The Mail on Sunday advert w/ "Saturday Night, Sunday Morning" CD promotion
4) Nivea for Men Energy Cream Q10 advert
5) Argos advert (With Richard E Grant, being FABULOUS.)
6) "Taxi" (2004) advert
7) Aunt Bessie's advert 
8) TV advert for the CD compilation album "Acoustic Songbook" ("3 CD's at a very special price"...a price so good, that we won't show you.)
9) TV advert for "Singles" by Travis
10) "What the Butler Saw" Promo (Soooo, it's basically an early "Come Dine with Me" for posh people? Okay!)
11) "Sponsored by Pizza Hut" bumper / "IS THAT NICK FROST?" Yes, that IS Nick Frost. Wait, what are you doing here? Get out of my house!

Inizialmente scettica, Joni si mette sulle tracce del padre e scopre che questi è Paul, un dongiovanni che gestisce un ristorante biologico alla periferia di Los Angeles. Quando le due madri lo scoprono, non resta loro che introdurre Paul all'intero nucleo familiare.

title: Don't Speed | Pay Attention | This Will Change Your Life
description:
You can wait, there is no point in speeding, you could risk someones or your own life when speeding. Pay attention to the road when you're driving, espacially in school zones.

Speeding results in:
Lives lost -- over 13,000 each year.
Work zone crashes and fatalities -- speed was a factor in 27 percent of fatal crashes in construction and maintenance zones in 2005.
Unsafe school zones -- compliance with lower speed limits is poor.
Economic costs -- speed-related crashes cost society over $40 billion annually, according to NHTSA. Every minute "gained" by speeding to a destination costs U.S. society over $76,000.
Speeding is often one of several risky factors in fatal crashes, because alcohol-impaired drivers are more likely to speed, and speeding drivers are less likely to wear seat belts. Alcohol, lack of seat belts and speeding can add up to a deadly combination.

Young males are the most likely to be involved in speeding-related crashes. According to 2007 NHTSA data, 39 percent of male drivers age 15-20 who were involved in fatal crashes were speeding at the time of the crash.

Tags
Stop Speeding, Slow Down, Pay Attention, This Will Change Your Life, Death, Jail Time, Don't Speed, Car Accident

title: TVA 5 anos 1996 - Vídeo Promocional - Super Canal TV - Arquivo
description:
Em 1996, a TVA completou 5 anos de existência.
Esse vídeo promocional, mostra a evolução da empresa durante os 5 primeiros anos de funcionamento, inclusive, destaca o lançamento da TVA Digisat (primeiro sistema de TV por assinatura via satélite digital do Brasil - Banda C) e o lançamento do satélite Galaxy 3R em 1995 que possibilitou a chegada da DirecTV Brasil no ano seguinte 1996 (Banda KU, que nessa época tinha como sócio controlador o Grupo Abril, dono também da TVA.
Os canais de TV paga estavam começando a chegar no mercado brasileiro:
1991: CNN, ESPN, THE SUPERSTATION, SHOWTIME, TNT;
1993: CARTOON NETWORK
1994: HBO BRASIL
1994: FOX, DISCOVERY CHANNEL, EUROCHANNEL
1995: HBO2, MTV LATINO, ESPN BRASIL, RTPI, CMT;

title: Remember the 80's Yo-Yo craze
description:
In 1989 the UK was gripped by Yo-Yo Fever and everywhere you looked, there they were. You couldn't open a newspaper or switch on a television with seeing Yo-Yos. Everyone knew about       Yo-Yos, they were those plastic discs on a string that went up and down, right? Wrong! Since the days of the depression in the USA, when the Yo-Yo craze swept America and kids all over the country entered contests and won bicycles and footballs, the Yo-Yo had been transformed into a precision instrument that can perform literally hundreds of tricks, both easy and very complicated. 

Here in the UK, the Yo-Yo craze was part of a Coca-Cola advertising campaign, which had been run for over 40 years in just about every country worldwide, some several times. As a result of the Yo-Yo craze in the UK, Coca-Cola, at the time part of Cadbury/Schweppes, increased their sales and literally put their brand in the hands of their target Youth Market. Over 4 million Coca-Cola trademarked Yo-Yos were sold in a 10 week campaign.

Yo-Yo contests were held all over the UK and the final contest held at Alton Towers, presented by the late Jeremy Beadle. Here is the story of the 1989 Yo-Yo campaign in the UK.

title: Si hubiera instrucciones para cumplir 30...
description:
"La verdad es que no importa si te has muerto una o dos veces, o ninguna; siempre estás empezando de nuevo. En el fondo no hay nada que hacer, siempre tendrás 18, porque eres joven solo una vez, pero inmaduro para siempre. No hay instrucciones para cumplir 30, pero si las hubiera, serían estas: 'Haz una lista de todo lo que no te gusta de ti y luego tírala, eres el que eres; y después de todo no es tan malo como te imaginas un domingo de cruda. Tira el equipaje de sobra, el viaje es largo y cargar no te deja mirar hacia delante; y además te jode la espalda. No sigas modas, en 10 años te vas a morir de vergüenza de haberte puesto eso de todas maneras'.

  'Besa a tantos como puedas, deja que te rompan el corazón. Enamórate, date en la madre y vuelve a levantarte. Quizá hay un amor verdadero, quizá no, pero mientras lo encuentras lo bailado ni quien te lo quita. Come frutas y verduras; neta, vete acostumbrando a que no vas a poder comer garnachas toda la vida. Equivócate, cambia, intenta, falla, reinvéntate, manda todo al carajo y empieza de nuevo cada vez que sea necesario. De veras, no pasa nada, sobretodo si no haces nada. Prueba otros sabores de helado, otras cervezas, otras pastas de dientes'.

   'Arranca el coche un día y no pares hasta que se acabe la gasolina. Empieza un grupo de rock ¿por qué no?, toma clases de baile, aprende italiano, perdona, usa una bicicleta, olvida, deja ir, decide quien es imprescindible. Mientras más grande eres, más difícil es hacer amigos de verdad, y más necesitas quien sepa quien eres sin que tengas que explicárselo; esos son los amigos, cuídalos y mantenlos cerca. Aprende que no vas a aprender nada, pero no hay examen final en esta escuela, ni calificaciones, ni graduación, ni reunión de ex alumnos, ¡Gracias a Dios!. Felices 30 viejo. Bienvenido al resto de tu vida'."

PELICULA EFECTOS SECUNDARIOS..

title: IKEA Het Sofa Experiment nr.5
description:
Het IKEA Sofa Experiment:
Kleine veranderingen. Groots effect.

Wil jij ook wel eens iets veranderen in de inrichting van je huis maar weet je niet waar beginnen? En zou ook jij het liefst willen dat deze aanpassingen vooral makkelijk zijn en weinig kosten? Wel, dan ben je niet alleen!

Daarom stelt IKEA je nu het Sofa Experiment voor. Hierbij laten we je het verhaal zien van 5 uiteenlopende families in België, die allemaal een probleem hadden met hun sofa. Maar dit om verschillende redenen: lelijk, versleten, niet gezellig, té klein of onhandig. 
Door simpelweg hun sofa te vervangen en enkele textielaccessoires toe te voegen zoals een tapijt, gordijnen, kussens of plaids, verkregen we een groots effect. En niet alleen in hun interieur, ook op hun humeur. 

Ontdek hun verhaal en laat je inspireren om ook jouw woonkamer deze herfst warm aan te kleden.

title: VINTAGE 1955 DODGE CAR COMMERCIAL WITH MISS AMERICA HOST - BERT PARKS
description:
Either fairly, or unfairly, I always thought of Bert as a carnival huckster. He shilled for the Miss America pagent - "OH, THERE SHE IS, MISS AMERICA" (his sugary sweet theme song could cause INSTANT DIABETES.) 

The last time I saw Bert, he was portraying a so-called carricature of his own personna. He was in the Matthew Broderick & Marlon Brando film "The Freshman." Bert Parks played Bert Parks, and was hired by Brando's character (a shady underworld type of character, with a heart of gold) to sing the introduction of the "Meal Of The Evening", which was a Komodo dragon. His song was a take-off of the Miss American theme. 

The closer the animal was to being extinct, the higer the price for the exclusive meal. In reality, in was a con job. The meal was not the Komodo dragon, it was chicken, and Bert Parks sang the introductory song to start the con job rolling along.

BECOMING A HUCKSTER 101 - PROFESSOR BERT PARKS teaching the course.

For more vintage pop culture, from the 1950's, 1960's & 1970's, you might enjoy visiting TV TOY MEMORIES http://www.tvtoymemories.com/FRONT_PAGE.html

title: 中条あやみ、セーラー服姿で街中を疾走！　「ポカリスエット」新CMキャラに　CM「Jump」編60秒バージョン＆メーキング映像
description:
★高画質★エンタメニュースを毎日掲載！「MAiDiGiTV」登録はこちら↓
http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=maidigitv

　ファッション誌「Seventeen」などで活躍するモデルで女優の中条あやみさんが、大塚製薬のイオン飲料「ポカリスエット」の新CMキャラクターに起用されたことが4月16日、明らかになった。中条さんは新CM「Jump」編でセーラー服姿で街中を疾走しており、「約500人のエキストラのみなさんと呼吸を合わせて全力疾走したときは、走る距離も長くてすごく大変でしたが、終わったときは達成感があり、とても楽しかったです」と笑顔で振り返った。18日から全国で放送。

　中条さんは「ミスセブンティーン 2011」でグランプリを受賞し芸能界デビュー。2011年9月から雑誌「Seventeen」（集英社）専属モデルとして活躍しており、12年にはドラマ「黒の女教師」（TBS系）で女優デビュー。昨年9月にはホラー映画「劇場版 零～ゼロ～」で映画初出演で初主演に抜てきされ注目を集めた18歳だ。

　「自分は、きっと想像以上だ。潜在能力をひき出せ。」をメッセージにした新CMは、高校の全校朝礼のシーンから始まる。中条さん演じる女子高生はつまらなそうに時間を過ごしていたが、校長が突然、ロックバンド「クイーン」の名曲「WE WILL ROCK YOU」を歌い出すと、一転、何かに駆り立てられるかのように学校から駆け出し、眠っていた潜在能力が花開く……というストーリー仕立ての内容になっている。

　CMは、学校や街の中、高層ビルの屋上、港などさまざまな場所で撮影された。どの場所のロケでも「走った」という中条さんは「想像以上にたくさん走ったので筋力も鍛えられました」と振り返っていた。なお、撮影に臨む中条さんに迫ったメーキングドキュメンタリー動画も公開する。

title: 臺灣觀光六大主題「讚！臺灣」美食篇(3分鐘版)； "Bravo! Taiwan" - FOOD(3min)；「いいね！台湾」―美食編
description:
臺灣觀光六大主題「讚！臺灣」美食篇(3分鐘版)； "Bravo! Taiwan" - FOOD(3min)；「いいね！台湾」―美食編。2014年觀光局製。

是什麼樣的魅力讓老外對臺灣讚不絕口？交通部觀光局2014年推出全新六大主題國際宣傳影片，以貼近真實的記錄形式，呈現外籍旅人在臺灣旅行的真實體驗，臺灣獨特多元的觀光魅力讓老外連聲稱「讚！」。

What is it that makes foreigners want to shout "Bravo!" when they experience Taiwan? This year the Taiwan Tourism Bureau has produced short promotional videos centered on six different themes, using a quasi-documentary method to present the actual experiences of foreign travelers in Taiwan. The films express how the island affects foreign tourists so much that their only response is, "Bravo!"

外国人が「いいね！」と絶賛して止まない台湾の魅力とは何でしょう？交通部観光局は、今年(2014年)新たに６つのテーマを題材にした海外向けプロモーションフィルムをリリースしました。外国人旅行者が台湾で体験する様子をよりリアルに描き、台湾の独特且つ多元的な旅行の魅力に「いいね！」と絶賛する様子を伝えています。

title: TBS Christmas Eve 1989 Part 9 - The Little Mermaid (1975) Part of Break 2
description:
MERRY CHRISTMAS! For your holiday entertainment we present to you what we believe are afternoon movie memories from over 20 years ago. Nowadays, TBS airs the perennial 1983 Christmas classic, "A Christmas Story," for a 24-hour period (a job previously held by TNT from 1997 until 2004 and in 2007) from Christmas Eve at 8pm ET until Christmas Day at 8pm. We go back now, however, to 1989, just after TBS introduced its "Entertainment with a Capital YES!...TBYES!" campaign. "A Christmas Story" aired (apparently) at 1:35pm ET, and an anime adaptation of Hans Christian Andersen's "The Little Mermaid" (for purposes of this video, I'm dating it with its original release year of 1975, although the film was dubbed in English in 1979), which probably aired due to the fact that Disney released their own version of the tale that year, followed at 3:35pm. Please enjoy!

1. TBS promo for "The Incredible Shrinking Woman" with Lily Tomlin
2. Two 15-second Cheerios commercials emphasizing its oat bran content not found in Post's Raisin Bran or Kellogg's Corn Flakes. It would be a while before we started hearing that it could help lower our cholesterol (along with a heart-healthy diet, of course).
3. Promo for the CNN Studio Tour in Atlanta, which is still going strong today, though with a subtle name change. http://www.cnn.com/tour/atlanta/
4. Dial soap commercial.
5. Promo for Sports Illustrated's Super Shape-Up Program video series, which I happen to own. The promo cuts off halfway in. The series was released by HBO Video and sponsored by Diet Pepsi. I can't see a late-80s HBO Video logo without expecting Diet Pepsi's "The Right One" commercial to follow it.
6. A brief message of Christmas greetings from all of us at NextG Entertainment.

Video footage courtesy of NextGeneration Enterprises, an entity "spun off" from the original NextG which is now a part of Cameo Entertainment Group. Site (up soon): http://www.cameofilms.com

description:
Midway Car Rental made a great car commercial for their Supercar rental business and it features a lot of references to internet memes at that time - funny - hard to do well but they did!
CARJAM TV Car Show -- Subscribe Now For The Best + Rarest Car Videos 
Website:          http://www.carjam.tv

Supercar is a term used most often to describe an expensive high end car. It has been defined specifically as "a very expensive, fast or powerful car".[1] Stated in more general terms: "it must be very fast, with sporting handling to match", "it should be sleek and eye-catching" and its price should be "one in a rarefied atmosphere of its own".[2]

 The supercar can take many forms including limited production specials from an "elite" automaker, standard looking cars made by mainstream companies that hide massive power and performance, as well as models that appeal to "hardcore enthusiasts" from "manufacturers on the fringe of the car industry".[3]

"Supercar" is also a label custom car retrofitters reserve for their showcase, one-of-a-kind project vehicles; typically these are very extensively-modified collectible muscle cars, sports cars or grand touring automobiles updated to the very latest "streetable" racing technology.[4][5]

Occasionally, the term Hypercar is used for cars that might be considered beyond the definition of "Supercar". This is even more difficult to define.
The Times for 11 November 1920 with the phrase "If you are interested in a supercar, you cannot afford to ignore the claims of the Ensign 6."[6] The Oxford English Dictionary also cites the use of the word in an advertisement for an unnamed car in The Motor dated 3 November 1920, "The Supreme development of the British super-car."[7] and defines the phrase as suggesting "a car superior to all others".

In the United States, the term "supercar" predates the classification of muscle car to describe the "dragstrip bred" affordable mid-size cars of the 1960s and early 1970s that were equipped with large, powerful V8 engines and rear wheel drive.[12] The combination of a potent engine in a lightweight car began with the 1957 Rambler Rebel that was described as a "veritable supercar".[13] "In 1966 the sixties supercar became an official industry trend"[14] as the four domestic automakers "needed to cash in on the supercar market" with eye-catching, heart-stopping cars.[15] Among the numerous examples of the use of the supercar description include the May 1965 issue of the American magazine Car Life, in a road test of the Pontiac GTO, and how "Hurst puts American Motors into the Supercar club with the 390 Rogue"[16] (the SC/Rambler) to fight in "the Supercar street racer gang" market segment.[17] The "SC" in the model name stood for "SuperCar".[18] The supercar market segment included regular production models[19] in different muscle market segments (such as the "economy supercar"[20]), as well as limited edition, documented dealer-converted vehicles.

During the late 20th century, the term supercar was used to describe "a very expensive, fast or powerful car with a centrally located engine",[25] and stated in more general terms: "it must be very fast, with sporting handling to match", "it should be sleek and eye-catching" and its price should be "one in a rarefied atmosphere of its own".[26]

大島優子、一人暮らしのOL役演じる　第一三共ヘルスケア『ミノン』CM「帰省」篇 

　女優の大島優子（26）、俳優の菅田将暉（22）がきょう24日オンエア開始のヤマハ発動機『TRICITY（トリシティ）』の新CMで初共演を果たした。

　昨年、AT限定小型二輪免許を取得した大島が、商品の楽しさを伝える「部長」として、菅田が「新入部員1号」として登場。大島が通りすがりの菅田に愛車を自慢し、前2輪が滑らかに傾く様子を「リーン！」と体を可愛らしく傾けながら表現する。これを見た菅田も思わず「リーン」と口ずさんでしまう内容。

　撮影では、大島の「リーン！」に菅田が照れ笑いするシーンも。菅田のボケに大島が真顔でツッコミを入れるシーンでは、大島の迫真の“真顔”に「びっくりするくらい怖い」と菅田がコメント。思わずNGを出してしまっていた。
