title: Carlitos El Dulcero - Rap dominicano
description:
Carlitos el dulcero, Rap dominicano 2015
http://indashop.tk
-Hey muchacho, dulcero!!! 
-Dígame señor 
-Cuál es tu nombre? 

Mi nombre es Carlitos y vendo dulce, 
para sobrevivir aunque mi vida no ha sido del nada dulce ha sido muy amarga 
y el destino me cobra a la corta lo que a los otros quizás a la larga, 
soy muy joven aunque la verdad 
he sentido la vejez del sufrimiento a mi corta edad pero usted entenderá 
que la vida es dura y se suda cuando la cruda realidad grita NECESIDAD. 
Sería bueno trabajar para progresar, mejorar y cambiar de mi status social 
pero lo que gano es para alimentar a mi familia que en casa siempre me han de esperar con él. Estomago partido, las tripas haciendo ruido 
porque esta es la hora que todavía no han comido 
esta es la hora que solo he vendido 2 dulces y tengo hambre 
¿A dónde se fue mi suerte? A donde? 
Si las gentes supieran con el cariño que lo hago 
para ganarme unos míseros centavos 
para sustentar esta vida inerte y evadir la fragancia rancia que me acosa con la muerte. 
Hay gentes que me ignoran, por mis aramos me catalogan 
como delincuente o que consumo droga 
no saben la razón de esta vida recia 
solo se fijan en mi sudor y esta cara sucia, 
muchos se burlan otros intentan humillarme 
pero no entienden que yo quisiera superarme 
que yo no elegí esta cadena para condenarme 
y la sociedad me ve como un problema debo resignarme. 
A ser marginado a caminar y no ser notado 
por el pasillo de los olvidados solo estoy vivo por 2 motivos 
por los cuales respiro por los cuales los dulces van conmigo. 

-Woww que penosa tu situación, no está estudiando? 
Se ve que eres un muchacho trabajador y con deseo de superarse y tus padres no te dan ayudas? 

Bueno, cuando yo tenía 10 años mi padre nos abandono, 
no se imagina cuanto nos dolió 
mi hermano pequeño no lo recuerda 
porque el tenia 2 años apenas cuando papi nos dejo, 
mi madre sufrió tanto que cayó en cama, 
tuve que soltar los estudios y coger la limpia bota para emprender el camino 
y dejar los juguetes para convertirme en el juguete del destino, 
yo mantengo a mi madre y a mi hermano 
con los dulces la vida me gano aunque pierdo la mía pero no hay un día 
en que las lagrimas no visiten la puerta de mis ojos por eso esta rojo algunos días. 
No he fácil la vida que llevo pero mi conciencia es limpia, 
aunque yo este sucio como un pordiosero 
no me atrevo a atracar, a robar ni matar prefiero sudar y honradamente trabajar yo quiero. 
Mi madre me ayudaba hace un tiempo pero se sentía cansada y en casa tuvo que quedarse 
y todo se complico cuando el doctor la reviso y le diagnostico un incurable cáncer, 
hay medicina que no puedo comprar, hay tratamiento que no puedo pagar 
son caros en exceso pero algo que no tiene precio 
son los abrazos de mi madre, su sonrisa y sus tiernos besos. 
Como quisiera que mi situación sea diferente 
un buen trabajo para que no me discrimine las gentes 
pero no entiende algo ilógico como la suciesa se refleja en la limpieza del político. 
Tome no pague lo que cuesta 
es que quiero regalarle un dulce por escucha lo que a mí me afecta 
pero yo solo quería que sepa 
que mi realidad no se palpar desde el asiento de su jeepeta.

title: Emotional AD to memorial discontinued Shanghai VW Santana (1983~2012)
description:
The Volkswagen Santana is a three-box sedan, based on the second-generation Volkswagen Passat (B2). It was first introduced in 1981 and is scheduled to remain in production (in China) until 2012.

In North America, it was also known as the Volkswagen Quantum. In Mexico, it was named the Volkswagen Corsar, while in Argentina it was sold as the Volkswagen Carat. In Brazil and other South American countries it was known as the Santana, while the Passat Variant B2 wagon was marketed as the Volkswagen Quantum. In Europe, the Santana name was dropped in 1985 (with the exception of Spain, where the Santana nameplate was retained) and the car was sold as a Passat. European production ended in 1988.

description:
From Chicago on The Station That Must Not Be Named (and I think this predates their going nationwide on cable), this was found at the end of an old Beta K-60 that unfortunately had been recorded over with worthless crap several times well into the 80s, this was the only 70s goodness that survived on it.

First up we have Ziebart Auto-Truck Rustproofing with some hand-drawn animation, then Close-Up toothpaste- put your money where your mouth is.  Then a high-tech looking Kawasaki SST-440 SnoJet on video, a slide for Mundelein College, The 8:00 Movie intro followed by some more commercials: Hostess cakes on 16mm (I also have a better-quality copy of this from a network show uploaded here), Creative Mirror Designs with what sounds like a live announcer at the end as he talks into the Liquid All commercial following that, when sadly the tape runs out.

title: TV2-reklame-blok fra omkring 1991
description:
Denne reklame-blok fra TV2 er dateret 1991, grundet en optagelse der er tideliger på båndet - men den kan også være fra før og mere sandsyndeligt efter 1991. 

Denne reklameblok er optaget fra TV2, hvor de viste filmen: de røde heste. Hvad alle selvfølgelig kan læse. Men for at alle kan google sig frem til denne video må jeg lige nævne det. Derefter kommer der en reklame for steff holberg pølser. 

Derfter bringes der en reklame for et vaskepulver kaldet radion micro. Hende der fremfører reklamen lyder som hende der lagde stemmen til "Dimsi" i Nødde-patruljen i DR´s Disney sjov.

Så kommer der reklame for beach boys, efterfulgt af en reklame for Vim. 

Derefter kommer der en reklame for isen Magnum fra Frisko, efterfulgt af en reklame for Falck.

Derefter kommer der en reklame for colgate tandbørste og derefter en banan reklame for Chiquita.

En reklame for vaskemidlet Sun Progress følger, hvorefter en reklame for libresse kommer.

Til sidst kommer der en klassisk reklame for Toblerone. Efterfulgt af en reklame fra tryg forsikring.

Holy Soda Commercial! Taylor Swift and Katy Perry have created some prettttty cool ads, but between Katy's Epic Pepsi Halftime Announcement and Taylor's kitten-centric Diet Coke spot, who do you think wins the title of Soda Commercial Queen? 

OK, let's get this soda party going with my girl, Taylor. Her Diet Coke commercial was literally one of the cutest things I've ever seen. First it was one kitten, then two and before you know it... we're in Cute Overload Zone.

But Tay's not the only cat lady on the block. Miss Katy Perry not only had cats, but she also had: glitter, sharks, robots.... truly the only word to describe it is EPIC. I mean how can you not watch the half-time show?

title: Mind, Body & Soul (1992) starring Wings Hauser - Trailer
description:
Wings Hauser battles monotone line delivery and Satanic cults in Mind, Body & Soul, a 1992 thriller by Rick Sloane (writer/director of the intentionally cheese-tastic Hobgoblins and the Vice Academy series).  We might have to track down a copy of this movie just to get the full effect of all these performances, but for now we'll consider this a best-worst-of reel.

John Stockton had already been playing for the Utah Jazz for eight years at this point, so it makes perfect sense that Hauser's character was named John Stockton for no apparent reason.

Trailer found on our VHS copy of The World's Oldest Living Bridesmaid, a romantic comedy that shares absolutely nothing in terms of theme, content, or atmosphere with this movie.

Find more cinematic gems in the zine I Love Bad Movies, available at http://www.ilovebadmovies.com and http://ksen.etsy.com, and follow us at http://facebook.com/badmovies for more bad-movie tidbits!

title: kabel eins Werbung mal anders
description:
FÜR MEHR INFOS AUFKLAPPEN
▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼▼
---------------------------------------------------

Hier wurde nochmal die kabel eins Werbepause vorgenommen, allerdings mit einen kleinen Nebeneffekt. Der Ton wurde um 30 Sekunden verschoben, so dass teilweise bizarre Sachen rauskommen. Ein erster Versuch, was Witziges anzustellen. Upload war am 12. März 2010.

URSPRÜNGLICHER BESCHREIBUNGSTEXT:
--------------------------------------------------------------------

Hier hab ich mal eines meiner Videos geopfert (kabel eins Werbung von November 2006) für ein kleines Experiment - hier hab ich Video und Audio vom Original-Video getrennt und in einem Programm hinzugefügt, jedoch die Audiodatei um 30 Sekunden verschoben. Dabei kommen einige witzige Sachen heraus, die teilweise auch passen.

Solch eine Art Videos mache ich das erste Mal, also keine strengen Kommentare, wenn das Video euch gegenüber nicht sehr gut ankommt. Es war immerhin der Versuch wert...

-----------------------------

title: Bugs Bunny Road Runner Show Half / Unusual Bumper / In the News- July 1983
description: ALL NEW!  First we have plugs for Donkey Kong cereal and Barbie.  Then the mid-show bumper mentions In The News (something i can't locate in any other recording I have of BBRR), then its an in The News segment (Which was not a part of the late run of BBRR) sponsored by Keebler Chips Deluxe.  After In The News are promos for Square Pegs and Private Benjamin and a plug for Burger Time (I remember one of my friends having that one).  Also notice, there is no intro to the second half of the show, they go right from the bumper into another cartoon...  that doesn't occur in any of the other recordings of BBRR that I have.

title: EVA HALINA RICH COMMERCIAL REEL
description:
Eva Halina's life has been a study overcoming adversity.
Born in Warsaw, Poland, she grew up under the cloud of a repressive
Socialist regime.When she was five, she lost her father when he was struck
by lightning while working as a lifeguard. That same year she was selected
to begin training for the Polish gymnastics team. For the next ten years,
her life revolved around the state run program culminating in her being
selected for the National team for the Olympics. The best all-round gymnast
in Poland and favored to medal in the uneven bars, a devastating knee
injury ended her dream of Olympic glory.
During her lengthy recovery, the petite gymnast began to grow, reaching
her present 5'9" in record time. No longer able to put stress on her knee,
she took to the air. At the age of 17, Eva became a trapeze artist & toured
Eastern Europe with the Julinek Circus.
After a year on the road, she decided to give modeling a try. Her Miss
Photo Poland crown led to several Polish film appearances, including the
critically acclaimed "Siren". Europe beckoned and she travelled to Norway,
Germany, Italy and France, working for such publications as Vogue, Elle,
Esquire and Cosmopolitan. She began doing commercials in Europe and,
finally, she decided to give the states a shot. She arrived in Miami with
$100, limited English and an audition for a Coors Light commercial.
Naturally, she booked the spot and, for the next 5 years, she was seen
"tapping the Rockies". Other spots for Diet Coke, Pepsi, Levis and many
soon followed.
She continued modeling around the world but on-camera work was taking up
more and more of her time. She has appeared on Friends, The Pretender, VIP
and The Drew Carey Show, in addition to the starring role of Eva Kirov in
the action-adventure series The Dream Team. She currently stars in the
Polish reality show, Wives of Hollywood.

title: Ana Maria Braga ensina a fazer o Arroz Doce Energia da Zaeli | Alimentos Zaeli
description:
Arroz Doce Energia

A apresentadora Ana Maria Braga mostra uma receita que, além de dar água na boca, é super fácil de ser preparada. Trata-se do Arroz doce feito com o Achocolatado em Pó Energia Zaeli, enriquecido com nove vitaminas e maior teor de cacau. Confira:

INGREDIENTES

• 2 xícaras de chá de ARROZ AGULHINHA ZAELI
• 1 xícara de chá de açúcar
• 1 litro de leite
• 2 litros de água
• 395 ml de creme de leite (1 lata) 
• 50 gramas de COCO RALADO ZAELI
• 1 xícara de chá de ACHOCOLATADO EM PÓ ENERGIA - ZAELI

MODO DE PREPARO

- Lave o arroz e coloque em uma panela com a água. Leve ao fogo até que fique macio e quase seco.
- Acrescente o leite, o açúcar, o achocolatado em pó e o coco ralado (reservando um pouco para polvilhar)
- Mantenha cozinhando em fogo brando por mais 20 minutos.
- Junte o creme de leite, deixe mais cinco minutos em fogo brando e desligue.
- Retire do fogo e coloque numa travessa para esfriar.
- Polvilhe o restante do coco ralado e leve ao refrigerador, sirva gelado.

Participação da Zaeli no Programa "Mais Você", com Ana Maria Braga.

#AlimentosZaeli #PedeZaeli #Zaeli #Zaelinho #Zaeli50Anos

title: Comcast "Rave Reviews" Pay-Per-View Previews, 1991
description:
Pay-Per-View Previews from Comcast Northeast Philadelphia's PPV preview channel, from spring 1991.  Includes the "How To Order" rap.  Yes, the "How To Order" rap.

This was when that system started collectively branding its Pay-Per-View offerings as "Rave Reviews".  I'm really curious to know if this stuff was used on any other Comcast systems, as it looks very well produced, but I recall seeing another Comcast system not using this branding.  At the same time they stopped promoting the actual PPV channel names to the point of covering them over when promos aired on the barker channel.  The only one they didn't try to cover up was Continuous Hits, which actually got its own animation.

For the curious, Continuous Hits was on 36, Cable Video Store was on 37, a local PPV channel using the Rave Reviews name was on 38, and Viewer's Choice was on 39.

title: If It's Delicious And Light: TSW Adverts & Gus Honeybun, 1992
description:
Bedknobs and Broomsticks comes to an end after at least twenty minutes too many, and we start off with yet more bloody laundry. This time it's Persil, with a fat scientist dancing around in a vaguely Beckettian cavern of washing machines, while singing a re-written version of "Reet Petite". That song actually made me hate this advert, because I had been genuinely frightened as a three-year-old by the nightmarish video for the 1986 reissue, which featured a claymation Wilson capering around and occasionally shapeshifting in an even more Beckettian landscape, with musical staves hanging in the air, bushes made of little singing mouths, and a terrifying effigy rolling his r's and at one point MELTING HIS FACE INTO A BABY'S FACE in the middle of it.

Then there's a corny but strangely likeable advert for Delight, a range of low-fat, low-cholesterol business that seems to have died out with the 20th Century, although I could be wrong. It's bloody hard to Google.

Next it's Rice Krispies, and Snap, Crackle and Pop, except it's COMPLETELY WRONG because Snap, Crackle and Pop are NOT BLOODY SUPERHEROES, they're little Keebler elf pixie whatever men. In their original configuration as pixies, they had (and have, having reverted a few years later) individual personalities. Not these guys. Here they're apparently beating up Robbie Rotten's dad, which serves him right for being such a rubbish villain. Although I have to wonder where Superman is, given that this is apparently Metropolis. A far more disturbing version had the Dim Patrol here played by actual pre-pubescent boys in rubber wigs. With the same voices. I don't know which version came first, but I'd wager it was the uncanny valley-tastic live action one because a) it's easier to comp in some animation over the top of extant footage than it is to remount and reshoot that entire scene for live-action shooting, and b) this version's shorter.

Next, a simpering woman explains gum disease with a tomato. She doesn't explain how similar a tomato is to the human gum. Those bouncy necks were soon pretty much standard on all decent toothbrushes.

Then there's an archetypal poncey perfume advert which seems to have been shot on film slathered in honey. It's from Vanderbilt, as is pointed out over and bloody over. Vanderbilt.

Then Chris Barrie voices for Smarties - which in the UK are little round discs of chocolate in thin sugary shells - and their latest promotion, Gruesome Greenies. Now, according to Robin Carmody ("it brings me the same kind of joy I always strive for in my writing"), this is from 25th May 1992. Why did they do a spooky-themed promotion in May, rather than, say, October? Only Smarties have the answer.

The final advert is for Burger King Kids' Club, their incorrect answer to McDonaldland. In contrast to that lot, BK have by now pretty much given up and gone home as far as the concept and characters are concerned, with literally every appearance they ever made consisting of this advert with a different promotional toy in the middle. All the "You Got It"s - the chain's main slogan at the time - smack of increasing desperation. I can't shake the feeling that the voice artist collapsed on the ground weeping at the end of the session.

That's the last advert, but there's also a rather unusual Gus Honeybun Birthday slot in which they've somehow managed to break the magic button, meaning at least one kid has to settle for bunny hops. An apparently drunk Gus' foil is the adorable Sally Meen, who had the misfortune of joining TSW in 1990. Later she joined GMTV as a weathergirl, and spent two years as the glamour stooge in Jim Davidson's Generation Game, which is a terrible thing to happen to anyone.

Once the birthdays are out of the way, Sally introduces the still relatively new (to us - it had only been on three years) Home and Away, which gets as far as the first bar of the theme tune before giving up. And that's the end of that tape. Having had a VCR for three years, we apparently still hadn't figured out that you can record things after other things. Vanderbilt.

title: Channel 4 (UK) Ads, Continuity and Junction (December 1999) (2)
description:
Another one. :)

CONTENTS!:
1) Amarula Cream ad (Partial) (I hardly drink that much at all and don't really like alcoholic drinks usually but this looks really tasty...so does Bailey's...oh gosh, I can legally drink now. Arg, someone help!)
2) TV ad for "Rancid Aluminium"
3) Magnet ad (Always found it annoying when they advertise Boxing Day sales just before Christmas. They have to, sure, but it kinda makes you think of what comes after Christmas rather than Christmas itself! Or at least to me, of course.)
4) Dollond & Aitchison ad ("...Marvellous!" This ad sure, sure is.)
5) TV ad for "Muppets from Space" (In this ad, it has the tagged-on tagline "The X-Mas Files"...I barely remember them advertising it this way. Was this advertised like that elsewhere in the world or just here? Weird. Not a bad film, though!)
6) The Salvation Army Christmas Appeal charity ad
7) Promo for "The Snowman" and "The Bear" (Looking forward to "The Snowman and The Snowdog" this year, on the subject of this!)
8) Channel 4 ident w/ announcement / Very, very small part of the into to "Bob and Margaret" / "Who's for another bruskie?" / "Bob & Margaret" title card / Channel 4 ID sting
9) Moben ad
10) Imperial Cancer Research Fund charity ad (Now running as Cancer Research UK)
11) "Bob and Margaret" title card / "Its really nice to have met you."

description:
亨利是個懷才不遇的編劇，日復一日過著放蕩不羈的生活，即便枕邊美女一換再換，他依然難忘舊情人凱薩琳娜。某天，亨利意外接到一個大案子，要將一本全球賣座的暢銷小說改編成劇本，而即將與他共同執筆的原著作者，竟然就是舊情人凱薩琳娜！亨利興奮不已，想趁此良機重新追回生命中的最愛；此時卻半路殺出了一名八歲女孩瑪德蓮娜，還自稱是他的女兒。為照顧這初來乍到的女兒，半本爸爸經也不懂的亨利，竟異想天開端出昔日把妹專用的拿手菜「紅酒燉香雞」來招待她，濃濃酒味卻讓八歲的瑪德蓮娜難以下嚥，只好偷偷開伙、還搞到火燒廚房。但最糟糕的是，亨利與凱薩琳娜好不容易復燃的愛情，似乎也將毀在這位天外飛來的小女孩手中。

title: 松本人志が清掃員役で出演！「タウンワーク」新CM「エレベーター」編、メーキング・インタビュー映像も
description:
★高画質★エンタメニュースを毎日掲載！「MAiDiGiTV」登録はこちら↓
http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=maidigitv

　お笑いコンビ「ダウンタウン」の松本人志さんが、リクルートの求人情報メディア「タウンワーク」のCMキャラクターに起用されたことが7月24日、分かった。松本さんが清掃員に扮（ふん）した新CM「エレベーター」編は27日から放送されるほか、次回作で松本さんと共演できる“激レアバイト”も募集する。

　新CM「エレベーター」編は、とある雑居ビルが舞台で、夏休みのバイトを相談しながらエレベーターに乗り込む男子大学生2人に、エメラルドグリーンのつなぎ姿で清掃をしていた松本さんが圧倒的な目力とともに「バイトするなら、タウンワーク！」と訴える……という内容。松本さんの登場により緊張感に包まれるエレベーター内の様子や、力強いコメントのあとに放つ松本さんのシュールな“つぶやき”などが見どころになっており、特設サイトでは24日からCM映像を先行配信する。

　“激レアバイト”は、定期的に貴重なバイト体験を提供する「タウンワーク」のキャンペーンで、今回はエキストラとして松本さんとCMで共演でき、アルバイト当日はCM制作の美術チームとともに撮影で使用する小道具の作成にも携わることができる。バイト時期は12月上旬、場所は関東圏を予定。応募は「タウンワーク」の公式サイト内から行い、27日から8月16日まで受け付ける。

2) Promo for the "Animaniacs Christmas Eve On The Hub" marathon (Good grief, that sounds like an amazing marathon, with such a fantastic show. Hub viewers of the US, have an awesome Christmas Eve...but hey, I'm sure you will do anyway! What a treat!)
3) Bratzillas ad
4) TV spot for the home video release of "Ice Age: Continental Drift" (I haven't seen this yet, but I looked at the back of the Blu-ray for this and it doesn't mention the Simpsons short that was attached to this film at all...quite disappointing.)
5) "Angry Birds: Star Wars" Jenga Death Star Game ad (Oh gosh, "Angry Birds", "Star Wars"...and JENGA? Oh its a copyrighted, corporate mish-mash here! Also, why buy one of these things when you can just gather around random stuff in your house and throw soft balls at it? There's your Angry Birds board game, with 100% less wallet drainage!)
6) TV ad for "Pirate 101" video game (From the gameplay footage they have here, it doesn't actually look bad for a family-targetted MMO!)
7) FurReal Friends "Bouncy" ad (Awww, that's so cute, it has a neck problem and constantly has seizures!)
8) TV ad for "Moshi Monsters: Moshlings Theme Park" video game
9) Arm & Hammer Spinbrush ad (Who'd of thought an ad for an electric toothbrush would be the most festive ad in these uploads today... o_o;;; )
10) Hub ID sting
11) Stompeez! infomercial
12) Promo for "Littlest Pet Shop" (That was a fun episode!)
13) Promo for "Hub's Naughty & Nice Awards"
14) "Coming Up Next" bumper for "Littlest Pet Shop"
15) "We're Back!" sting w/ "Littlest Pet Shop"

title: BOUND　Works　（フロムA CMソング 80年代後期）
description:
フロムAのCMソングで知られたこの曲。ためしに私の周囲の人間に「昔こういう曲があったんだけど知っている？」と聞いてみたら、みんな「知っている」。中には「忘れられん」、「あのバンドはどなったの？」、「レコード持ってる」、「テープにとってある」などの答えもありました。
BOUNDは、この歌で人気が上昇するなかで突如の解散。私たちの前から消えてしまったと記憶しています。その意味で、この曲も「悲運の名曲」だったといえます。
ただし、メンバーの方たちは、今でも音楽活動をされているので、関心のある方たちは調べてみてください。

・クルマは愛だ。
・ニュー・スカイラインに走りのハッチバック登場。ポール・ニューマン、人生の楽しみ方を知っている男。
・レーサー、ポール・ニューマンの本能はスカイラインに狼の匂いを嗅ぎつけた。
・どうしても、男たちはスカイラインの魅力に　まいってしまうのだろうか。
・「スカG」と、最初に呼んだのは誰だ・・・スカイラインの走りにスーパーシルエットを見たのだろうか。
・スカイラインRSターボ登場。噂の4バルブDOHCターボは190馬力だ。
・スカイライン史上最強のスカイライン。190馬力の走りに、反響も史上最強だった。
・「ミスター ニューマン、このクルマ　なんていう名前？」　「スカイライン！　乗ってみるかい？」
・悔しいけれど、オフィスでもカフェテラスでも避暑地でも、絵になってしまう男にスカイラインはよく似合う。
・新しい男へ、新しいGT。「ポール・ニューマン・バージョン」誕生。
・優しいという事は、つまり、男らしいという事だ。パワーがあるからクールになれる。
・「Hey！Let's Go for Long Drive」　ニッサン・スカイラインには、走りを愛するハートがある。
・走りにクオリティを求め続けてきた・・・　ニッサン・スカイライン。
・スカイラインの走りは、いつでも、どこでも微笑んでいる。

title: Kim Kardashian's T-Mobile 2015 Super Bowl Commercial - VIDEO!
description:
Victoria's Secret Super Bowl Ad ►► http://youtu.be/37WhPw9v3jw
More Celebrity News ►► http://bit.ly/SubClevverNews

Kim Kardashian Premieres her Superbowl Ad for T-Mobile while visiting Conan Obrien last night…and it got the whole world laughing. Get out your Popcorn…you don’t want to miss this!

There’s been a lot of talk surrounding the 2015 Superbowl. Rumors have been swirling about Katy Perry’s half time performance, the NFL is up in arms over the alleged deflate-gate scandal. And how can we not mention the two hunky quarterbacks, Russell Wilson and Tom Brady, that are facing off on Sunday’s game. But in the midst of all of that, in classic Kardashian style, Kim Kardashian got the world buzing about her last night. 
While making an appearance on Conan Obrien’s show, she premeired her T-mobile superbowl commercial…well a sneak peek of it!
In a faux PSA, set to sokmber piano music, Kim very seriously explains the tragedy that takes place occurs when wireless companies take back unused data from customers. The reality star is then seen taking selfies in many different places— places she says you could see her if you still had all your unused data. Take a look:

I’m not sure if my favorite part of that is at the very begining when they introducer her as Kim, famous person or at the end when she stares at the camera and says "save the data." As if she is going to say “Save the Whales” or something noble.
Either way, it’s hard to deny the hilarity of the ad, which comes out right before the release of her selfie book titled “Selfish”. 
It seems like Kim was excited about the ad because she tweeted "so excited!" before the Conan show on Monday for all of her 28.1 million followers to see.
But we want to know if the ad got you excited? Do you think Kim makes herself more likeable by poking fun at herself and her love of selfies? And, do you think it’s better than her 2011 Sketchers Superbowl commercial? Let us know what you think in the comments below and don’t forget to subscribe! And if you can’t get enough of superbowl commercials click right over here to check out the Victoria Secret's Super Bowl Commercial…you know you don’t want to miss that. I’m your host Danielle Robay, thanks for watching Clevver news and I’ll see you next time!

title: 小栗旬が桃太郎演じるCM第4弾公開！ついに鬼ケ島上陸「Episode.3」編（4分バージョン）
description:
★高画質★エンタメニュースを毎日掲載！「MAiDiGiTV」登録はこちら↓
http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=maidigitv

　俳優の小栗旬さんが桃太郎を演じているペプシのテレビCM「桃太郎」シリーズの第4弾が7月11日から放送される。桃太郎一行がついに鬼ケ島に上陸し、黒鬼と戦う姿が描かれている。

　同CMシリーズは、2014年3月から放送を開始。第1弾「Episode．ZERO」編で、桃太郎が犬、猿、キジを仲間にして鬼ケ島に旅立ち、続く「Episode．1」編では、桃太郎が一人で鬼に挑み敗れた過去、「Episode．2」編では、仲間である「犬」の生い立ちから桃太郎と出会うまでが描かれた。

　新しい第4弾「Episode．3」編は、キジに焦点が当てられる。キジと双子の兄「カラス」は、鳥の王国の戦士として誕生し、キジは「愛」で民を守り、カラスは「力」で一族を支配していた。ある日、さらなる「力」への欲望に負けたカラスは、強大な力を求めて鬼の仲間となり、自らも鬼と化してしまう。そして、鬼ケ島に上陸した桃太郎一行と対峙（たいじ）する……というストーリー。30秒と60秒のバージョンがある。

　小栗さんは、同シリーズについて「日本ではできないようなことだったり、普段の撮影スタイルとは違うようなことをいつも経験させてもらえます。周りのみんなから、うらやましがられる作品になっているので、そういうこともひっくるめて、すごく刺激的な現場だと思います」とコメント。新CMについては「とうとう鬼ケ島に到着して鬼との戦いが始まるので、かなりいろいろなことが変化してる。生まれ変わった新生・桃太郎が見せられるんじゃないかと思っています」とアピールしている。

　BS・CSでは、4分バージョンが13日から放送される予定で、キジとカラスの細かいエピソードとともに、キジの複雑な心理描写や奪われた兄の心を取り戻すために戦いの決意をもって鬼ケ島へ向かう姿が描かれている。9日から公式サイトで先行公開される。

title: 木村文乃、CMで歌声披露　新ノンアルコールソーダのイメキャラに
description:
★高画質★エンタメニュースを毎日掲載！「MAiDiGiTV」登録はこちら↓
http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=maidigitv

　女優の木村文乃さんが、酒風味でアルコール度数0．00%の炭酸飲料「フォレスティ　森のソーダ＜レモン＆ライム＞」（サントリースピリッツ）のイメージキャラクターに起用され、新CMに出演することが9日、明らかになった。木村さんは、新CM「森の香り篇」で、「森の香りがする～」「ふぉれ ふぉれ ふぉれ フォレスティ～」といった不思議な歌を気持ちよさそうに口ずさんでいる。

　新CMは「恋人と2人きりで過ごす森の中」という設定で撮影され、リラックスした木村さんが歌を口ずさみ、「森が香るノンアルコールソーダ、フォレスティ。サントリーから」というナレーションで締めくくられる。

　木村さんは、撮影前に歌の自主練習をし、「リラックスという部分は意識しましたが、落ち着いた後にちょっと楽しくなるような雰囲気をスタッフの皆さんが作ってくださったので、私も楽しく歌うことができたと思います」とにっこり。自身の普段のリラックス方法について「何も考えずにボーッとすることでしょうか。日々の仕事の中でいろんなことを考えてしまうから、他の時間はなるべく考えないようにしています」と明かしていた。

　「フォレスティ　森のソーダ＜レモン＆ライム＞」は、甘さ控えめで、レモンとライムの味わいと、ジンを思わせる風味に、森に漂う香り成分を加えたノンアルコールソーダ。9日から全国で発売される。

title: A League of Their Own - Official Movie Trailer
description:
The All-American Girls' Professional Baseball League was founded in 1943, when most of the men of baseball-playing age were far away in Europe and Asia fighting World War II. The league flourished until after World War II, when, with the men's return, the league was consigned to oblivion. Director Penny Marshall and screenwriters Lowell Ganz and Babaloo Mandel re-create the wartime era when women's baseball looked to stand a good chance of sweeping the country. The story begins as a candy-bar tycoon enlists agents to scour the country to find women who could play ball. In the backwoods of Oregon, two sisters -- Dottie (Geena Davis) and Kit (Lori Petty) -- are discovered. Dottie can hit and catch, while Kit can throw a mean fastball. The girls come to Chicago to try out for the team with other prospects that include their soon-to-be-teammates Mae Mordabito (Madonna), Doris Murphy (Rosie O'Donnell), and Marla Hooch (Megan Cavanagh). The team's owner, Walter Harvey (Gary Marshall) needs someone to coach his team and he picks one-time home-run champion Jimmy Dugan (Tom Hanks), who is now a broken-down alcoholic. After a few weeks of training, as Dugan sobers up, the team begins to show some promise. By the end of the season, the team has improved to the point where they are competing in the World Series (which is no big deal, since there are only four teams in the league). - Paul Brenner

title: Riders In The Sky: America's Favorite Cowboys, Grammy Winning Music and Comedy
description:
http://www.eaglestalent.com/Riders-in-the-Sky -Eagles Talent Presents Riders in The Sky. To book the group Riders in the Sky visit their profile page.

Riders In The Sky are truly exceptional. By definition, empirical data, and critical acclaim, they stand "hats & shoulders" above the rest of the purveyors of C & W -- "Comedy & Western!" For thirty years Riders In The Sky have been keepers of the flame passed on by the Sons of the Pioneers, Gene Autry and Roy Rogers, reviving and revitalizing the genre. And while remaining true to the integrity of Western music, they have themselves become modern-day icons by branding the genre with their own legendary wacky humor and way-out Western wit, and all along encouraging buckaroos and buckarettes to live life "The Cowboy Way!"

Riders In The Sky are exceptional not just in the sense that their music is of superlative standards (they are the ONLY exclusively Western artist to have won a Grammy, and Riders have won two), but by the fact that their accomplishments are an exception to the rule as well.

description: For a few years, 2001-2004, Richard Earl succeeded in rallying key auto execs of General Motors on their rich design history. Being the standard-bearer of Harley Earl's automotive styling legacy, Richard vocally presented his research findings on America's automotive design legacy to many of McCann-Erickson advertising execs and Buick brand managers, and his idea went on to light a fire under a powerful new GM exec, Bob Lutz, who fast-tracked the Harley Earl TV ad campaign into reality. "It was amazing, for GM is legendarily slow moving but Lutz quickly pushed a new idea through the system to align Buick's live spokesman, Tiger Woods, alongside screen actor John Diehl, who went on to play Harley Earl in all the TV ads. These commercials were filmed by leading Hollywood director, Tony Scott," said Richard Earl who also signed the legal contract to start the ad campaign and acted all along as a consultant on the campaign. Richard continued saying, "the agreement allowed GM's Buick brand, and their advertising agency McCann-Erickson, the legal right to use 'Harley Earl's name, likeness and image' for a 5-year period. title: Government Surveillance Through Your Smartphone
description:
Obama offered a robust defense of newly revealed surveillance programs on Friday as more classified secrets spilled into public, complicating a summit meeting with China's new president focused partly on human rights and cybersecurity.


Mr. Obama departed from his script at a health care event in California to try to reassure Americans that he had not abused government authority by collecting telephone call logs and foreigners' e-mail messages. But the disclosure hours later of secret contingency planning to target other countries for possible cyberattacks made his get-together with President Xi Jinping later in the day all the more awkward because cyberattacks by the Chinese are high on the American agenda.

The latest of three documents published over three days by the British newspaper The Guardian added to the understanding of the Obama administration's approach to national security in an age of multifaceted threats and became another factor in the renewed debate over the balance between privacy and security.

The identity of the person who gave those documents to The Guardian and The Washington Post is not known, but The Post has described its source as a career intelligence officer angry at "what he believes to be a gross intrusion on privacy" by the Obama administration.

Once a critic of President George W. Bush's hawkish policies, Mr. Obama was ready with an explanation for why he has preserved and extended some of them when a reporter asked him at the health care event if he could assure Americans that the government was not building a database of their personal information. "Nobody is listening to your telephone calls," Mr. Obama said. "That's not what this program's about."

But he argued that "modest encroachments on privacy" were "worth us doing" to protect the country, and he said that Congress and the courts had authorized those programs.

A National Security Agency telephone surveillance program collects phone numbers and the duration of calls, not the content, he said. An Internet surveillance program targets foreigners living abroad, not Americans, he added.

"There are some trade-offs involved," Mr. Obama said. "I came with a healthy skepticism about these programs. My team evaluated them. We scrubbed them thoroughly." In the end, he concluded that "they help us prevent terrorist attacks."

But the disclosures united liberal Democrats and libertarian Republicans in accusing him of abandoning values he once espoused. "We believe the large-scale collection of this information by the government has a very significant impact on Americans' privacy, whether senior government officials recognize that fact or not," Senators Ron Wyden of Oregon and Mark Udall of Colorado, both Democrats, wrote in a joint response to the president's remarks.

Senator Richard J. Durbin, the Senate's No. 2 Democrat and an Obama ally from Illinois, rebuffed the president's contention that Congress had been kept abreast of the programs, saying only a handful of top leaders are regularly briefed.

"To say that there's Congressional approval suggests a level of information and oversight that's just not there," he said in an interview. He added that the sort of data mining revealed in recent days "really pushes the role of government to the limit."

Advocates of Congressional intervention said public pressure could revive legislation to at least force more transparency about the programs. "The timing has never been better to revisit our past decisions," said Senator Mike Lee, a Utah Republican.

But it was not clear whether there would be a popular backlash to the programs beyond some outrage on Twitter and Facebook, and even critics like Mr. Durbin were skeptical. Many Americans interviewed around the country on Friday shared concerns about their civil liberties but expressed a certain grudging resignation as well.

In Congress, the main vehicle for any changes, a reauthorization of the 1978 law that created the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court, passed only last December and is not due for renewal for five years. During the debate last winter, the Senate voted on a bipartisan basis to reject amendments to force transparency or curtail surveillance.

Moreover, beyond Mr. Durbin, Congressional leaders and senior lawmakers on the intelligence committees expressed few qualms. The House speaker, John A. Boehner, Republican of Ohio, said Mr. Obama must be more forceful in explaining the programs but declined to discuss his own position. Senator Harry Reid of Nevada, the Democratic majority leader, dismissed concerns. "Everyone should just calm down and understand this isn't anything that is brand new," he said.

title: Mind-boggling Commercials From Classic TV
description:
https://twitter.com/McFartnuggets
http://mcfartnuggets.blogspot.com
http://www.facebook.com/McFartnuggets

You know a commercial is old when it's about the dentist. Not about a toothpaste or floss, just the concept of dental hygiene provided by a tooth care professional. It's amazing dentists ever got popular with ads like these. I mean really, what was the point of showing this kid assaulting a foul mouthed woman walking her dog twice? 

In the second commercial we see another classic toilet paper commercial from before the Baby Face Killa's reign of terrors was uncovered. This may have been before he even started murdering, who can really be sure of that? This does give a nice insight into his psyche though. The events in this ad may have been one of the contributing factors to his descent into madness. People just took bites of his toilet paper and then begged him to take a swing at them knowing he legally couldn't. That ain't right.

After that, a commercial that faced the issue of alcoholic firefighters. Not something we hear about much these days, but apparently it was sort of a big deal a few decades ago. Apparently, a pet store in New York caught fire and one of the firefighters thought the lady who worked in there was an orangutan because the flames had burnt her hair and made it an orangey hue. This obviously raised a lot of questions about the value of life and whether or not the firefighter should have put his full effort into saving what he perceived to be a primate as if it were a human (which it was). This was back when coffee commercials tried to get political. Thank god that didn't last.

title: WDIV Detroit: July 30, 1990: Tiger Baseball, Harwell, Sparky
description:
Orignally aired on Monday evening, July 30, 1990. WDIV is the NBC affiliate in Detroit, Michigan and at the time had the rights to air Detroit Tiger baseball games.

In this clip are some of the commercials that aired durng the Tigers-Yankees game that evening.

First, Jim Varney as Ernest P. Worrell in an ABC Warehouse commercial. Then, Ernie Harwell in a spot for Citizen's Insurance; look for the Tigers Hall of Fame poster. 

George Kell then pauses ten-second for station identifcation and there are the graphics coming into and exiting the inning. This is followed by a spot for Eagle with Jack Klugmann and Tony Randall reprising their roles from the Odd Couple while playing "Duck Hunt."

Sparky Anderson is in a commercial for your "Local Metro Detroit Ford Dealers" and George Kell runs down the upcoming Tiger TV schedule. The end of the inning is shown, followed by a promotional event at an upcoming Tiger game.

Finally, there is a baseball-themed Kroger spot, a Bernie Smilovitz promo and then a Bernie voice-over for the sponsors of Tiger baseball.

title: TV2-reklame blok fra ca. 1991
description:
Denne reklame blok er ca fra 1991, da den viser en reklame fra filmen "Strømer i børnehaveklasse". Denne film havde premiere i USA i 1990, men dengang havde film tendens til at komme til Danmark mange måneder senere.

Reklamerne der optræder i denne reklame-blok:

* Halveret reklame for falck. 

* En trailer for "strømer i børnehaveklassen"

* Reklame for Trekroner margarine. 

* Reklame for bandet Gasolin: Rabalderstræde - forever CD.

* reklame for Dimension two in one shampoo. Shampoo og balsam i et (ja den har vi aldrig hørt før).

* Reklame for Philips energisparepære. 

* Reklame for denivit tandrens produkt.

title: Boomerang (UK) TV Ads and Continuity (September-October 2004) (4)
description:
COOOOOOOOOOONTEEEEEEEEEEEEEEENTS!

He was out to make a COOOONTEEENTS!

Didn't care what ha--yeah, the joke's getting flat now. CONTENTS!:
1) "There's More After This" bumper (with Tex Avery's Screwball Squirrel...doing...yeeeeah...)
2) Promo for the Movie Matinee showing of "Tom & Jerry: The Magic Ring"
3) Pooh & Friends Playhouse playset (The voiceover artists for the Winnie the Pooh characters are getting reeeeeeally, reeeeeeally stale ;) )
4) Kinder Surprise ad w/ Mole Mission toys promotion ("A secret never to be told...", just before they tell us. Word-for-word.)
5) Fisher Price Dora the Explorer toys ad (Kinda weird to think that Dora got as popular as it did in the UK. I can understand it being popular in the US but its kinda strange to think that Dora got just as popular here too. I was 12, nearing 13 at this point, I didn't care for any preschool show except those I grew up with when I was the right age. BBC's "Spider!" ftw!)
6) Bratz Funky Fashion Makeover toys
7) Weetos ad w/ "All Grown Up" promotion (I don't know what's more patronising, how annoyingly handled this ad's done or having to remember that "All Grown Up" actually existed. It wasn't that the aging of the characters ruined it, its that Nickelodeon clearly didn't give a shit imo. "Rugrats" had great characterizations and humour and stylish animation and was always a fun show to watch when it was at its peek. "All Grown Up" was just stupid, dated and soulless in comparison because it was clearly mean't to target those just as old as the characters on the show but without a sense of variety or fun or...anything really interesting besides, oh, its the Rugrats cast but 10 years older. Big whoop. Nice work, Nickelodeon.)
8) The Dandy ad (British humour comics. For kids. If you want a crash course in how badly to talk down to kids, read one of the newer ones of these. You'll know then.)
9) "Tooth" home video release ad (2004 was such a strange year. So, so strange.)
10) Lego Duplo Police Station ad
11) Promo for "The Powerpuff Girls" (An unappealing promo for what was, at its peak at least, a very entertaining show)
12) "Coming Up Later" bumper
13) "And Now For More" bumper w/ Tweety and Monster Tweety (?) (Finally a different one of these! And I just love how the cackle syncs in well with the music by the end of this, so memorable... :D)

title: nie ma pan kutasa, nie ma pan grzyba...
聖誕感人短片 Monty The Penguin
description:
新闻线上报 Online Breaking News
感人圣诞短片！

影片中，小男孩Sam有个形影不离的好朋友，一隻可爱的企鹅Monty，他们一起生活、一起出游，甚至还看了电影，直到圣诞节时，Sam送了Monty一份礼物，是另一隻可以与牠作伴的企鹅！牠们见面时甚至还开心的玩在一起。然而，等Sam的妈妈走进房间，一切才真相大白，原来Sam拿在手中的是两隻娃娃，分别是Monty与新的企鹅娃娃，这也暗示着原来Monty只是Sam幻想中的好朋友。
根据《镜报》的报导，原来这段名叫「企鹅Monty」（Monty the Penguin）的影片，是英国百货公司John Lewis的圣诞广告。心理医师Sheila Keegan表示：「这则广告中有很多小小的感动，也许第一时间裡你不会注意到它们，但它们却合力带给你一个大家都想要却不常实现的完美圣诞节。」
网友在看过影片后也纷纷发表意见，很多人觉得这真是太可爱了，有人说自己从来没有因为广告而哭的，不过也有人半开玩笑的表示，现在的小孩其实比较喜欢iPad当作礼物。

title: My Lil' Reminder Infomercial
description:
What they're selling:
A digital recorder, which is like an MP3 player except it records instead of playing back and can only hold one 30-second track so you can leave yourself reminders in audio form. "Shit, where did I put my digital recorder? Fuck!"

The hyperbole:
The scene opens with a senile grandma wandering around a parking lot. Weighing her options, which are searching for her car using a systematic procedure or talking to herself out loud before grabbing her head in frustration, she chooses the latter.

Sadly, if you're constantly forgetting things, lack the problem-solving skills to compensate, and cannot manage enough insight into your own uselessness to carry around a pen and paper with you at all times, then you may have advanced Alzheimer's Disease. You have no business wandering around a parking lot unescorted, let alone getting behind the wheel of a car or operating a digital recording device.

The reality:
We must admit, though, that the bit with the guy using it for storing driving directions was pretty convincing. If we ever sense that our ambient levels of smiling doucheness are running low, we'll be sure to place an order.

Of course, that's assuming the thing works properly. According to people who actually used the product:

"Piece of Junk"

"... you have to practically stick the thing inside your ear to hear it."

"On Friday I told my wife that she urgently had to get her medication from the pharmacy ... She recorded the message on her recorder (I saw her do it) ... she couldn't play back what was on the recorder. It was too late to go to any pharmacy ... My wife didn't get her medication. The funeral was Monday."

Source: Cracked.com

title: Coca-Cola Arctic Home: Canada
description: The Coca-Cola Arctic Home is the world's first temperature-controlled installation created to raise awareness of the polar bear's disappearing habitat. Inside the display is a sculpture of two polar bears, surrounded by real water. By pledging to reduce their carbon footprint or spreading awareness of the cause via video, text or Twitter, individuals could decrease the temperature inside the Arctic Home, keeping the polar bear's habitat frozen, while building awareness of the effects of global warming. The habitat traveled across Canada in February and March 2013 as a part of Coca-Cola's global Arctic Home initiative in partnership with WWF-Canada.

title: First Option Location Studio | Showreel 2011
description:
2011 show reel for First Option Location Studio
Film, TV, Photo & Event Hire Location | London
http://www.studiohirefirstoption.com
020 7739 0132

Situated in a private courtyard in the heart of Shoreditch, First Option is a versatile 2000 sq ft converted Victorian zip and suspender factory that has served as a highly acclaimed hire location for over thirty years. The studio is designed specifically for film, TV and stills, but is also a great event space. First Option comprises a 1000 sq ft split level space adjoining a 500 sq ft bespoke kitchen together with a smaller 230 sq ft prep kitchen. Within the main studio space - accessible via a spiral staircase - is an additional 204 sq ft mezzanine with 30 ft of built in desks and work tops, ideal as a production office or as a storage/ holding area.

Both the studio space and the main kitchen have high pitched roofs, with exposed Scotts pine roof trusses and sanded wooden floors. Our fabulous main kitchen has marble and wooden work tops, along with many features designed specifically for shooting purposes; including a mobile island with built in hob, and a glass lighting balcony – great for lighting the kitchen from outside and therefore minimising the need for lighting cranes. The studio is ideal for shooting daylight and has an abundance of natural light from both the north and the south, but also can achieve almost full blackout.

title: Rumbo a Brasil 2014 - Publicidad Uruguaya Copa Mundial Brasil 2014
description:
"La fiebre mundialista está entre nosotros" 

Un extraño virus está afectando a los uruguayos. Todavía no se sabe bien cómo se transmite, ni cómo se origina.

Con una fuerte apuesta a la realización fílmica, "La fiebre mundialista está entre nosotros", es la nueva campaña publicitaria de Nuevo Siglo de cara al Mundial 2014, en la que médicos uruguayos estudian el caso de una epidemia que afecta a los ciudadanos Uruguayos.


La "orgumildad" charrúa

 Cablevisión salió a la cancha con su nueva campaña para promocionar el Mundial, que emitirá en directo, donde expresa su "manera de vivir el mundial". 
un motivador hincha expone ante una tribuna de fanáticos, las razones para sentir "orgullo" por la selección...pero con la dosis necesaria de "humildad". De esa conjunción se crea el hashtag #ORGUMILDAD, sobre el que seguramente la empresa de cable "calentará" su campaña en la previa del mundial. Luisito Suárez fue el primero en tuitearlo.
La campaña se desarrollará en gráfica, vía pública, TV, radio y online, pero demás de la campaña 360°, se sumará un fuerte trabajo en redes sociales.
"En Cablevisión estamos trabajando en la estrategia Mundial 2014 desde hace varios meses, para que nuestros clientes puedan vivir una experiencia inolvidable en cada uno de los partidos, desde la comodidad de sus hogares, con la mejor calidad de imagen y sonido. Por eso en la primera parte del año trabajamos en una promoción especial con una oferta atractiva para que nadie se quede afuera del Mundial.  Ahora, con la campaña #ORGUMILDAD coronamos este camino hacia Brasil reflejando el sentir de cada uruguayo en esta Copa del Mundo. Como marca, queríamos estar cerca de nuestra gente y, sin dudas, lo conseguimos", explica Gisella Tomasi, gerente comercial de Cablevisión.

title: 9 most crazy PS2 commercials of all time
description:
It's been 15 years since the Playstation 2 hit the market and we still have fond memories of that second Sony console. Over the years of the PS2 Sony has made some of the weirdest commercials ever made... have a look!

1. Bambi – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T4tOvkvCvwQ 
For some reason David Lynch made a PS2 commercial in which a deer demolishes a truck. Why? Because the Playstation 2 is a different place, with different rules. 

2. Delivery guy – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4zU6uwcEWa8 
A delivery guy, who turns out to be a chick, comes to some guys Motel room to bring a PS2 and play some games. The lyrics of the song in the background are amazing by the way... 

3. Lost for words – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=msMehuZo3x8 / https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h28Kbdfmvbk 
Another commercial shot by David Lynch. We don't even have a clue what we are looking at here... How the hell is this an actual commercial? 

4. Get on board – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jk354q3oPlc
We don't even get to see the console or any games in this commercial. But hearing the song “Get on board” and seeing people fighting to reach the top of a human mountain, is a beautiful way of explain the struggle to reach the top of the leaderboards... isn't it? 

5. Epic game commercial – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=25pGBIQI46c
This Japanese Playstation 2 commercial is pretty cool. Sony introduces some of the game characters which will be featured in PS2 games. Can you imagine a modern version, with modern game characters? That would be freaking epic! 

6. Missing piece – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iFnDAGO2Wa4
Sony used a commercial about an eskimo talking about a missing piece of a jigsaw puzzle. Stating you don't need eye sight, but you do need vision. Yup, we guess drugs were easily accessible around the Sony offices back in those days. 

7. Fleas – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uvb5myzohN8

For some reason a video about the fictive conditioned life of a flea actually is a Playstation 2 commercial. Sure, what they mean is that you can escape your regular life with a PS2, but this is way too philosophical in our opinion. 

8. Playstation 9 – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UZejZiZX9_M 
Let's make a commercial about the future of Playstation. We paint a picture of a Playstation 9 and in the end we will give you it's predecessor, Playstation 2. What a way to kill the hype... 

9.  African safari – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gA1jOD-MBxE 
Young girls and sports mascottes? Stockbrokers and a pit crew? After watching this for 30 seconds we still have no idea what they are talking about. Fun anyone? Yes please.

Do you have fond memories of the PS2 era? Let us know in the comments below!

title: KCRA Channel 3 There 1983.mp4
description:
A 2:30 promo that never aired!  I made this one night messing around in KCRA's post-production department.  I took the custom music that most stations got from NBC, combined with a whole mess on one-inch videotape borrowed from the promotion library and a 17-year-old's desire to learn.

Thought it was terrible and never showed it to anyone.  One day about 4 years later, I happened to be dubbing it in Engineering and the promotion manager saw it and wondered why I never showed it to him.  He said he would have aired it or at least used it somewhere.  Oh, well.....

A couple of years ago, I found that someone had uploaded a bad-quality copy to you-tube.  I really wonder where it came from.  I had the only copy of it in existance.  When I left KCRA in 1992, I thought I took the only copy with me.

title: Breakfast Recipe-Cornflakes Choco Walnut Muffin (Kellogg’s Waale Guptaji ka "LOL Wala Nashta")
description:
Recipe: Cornflakes Choco - Walnut Muffin

Ingredients  :
½ Cup melted butter
½ Cup condensed milk
2 Tsp honey
2 Tbsp castor sugar
1 Cup crushed cornflakes
¾ Cup refined flour (maida)
¼ Tsp baking soda
¼ Tsp baking powder
2 Tbsp cocoa powder
2 Tbsp chopped walnuts
2 Tbsp golden raisins (kishmish)
1 Tsp vanilla essence
Butter for greasing
15 paper cups

Directions :
1. Mix all the ingredients  in a bowl and pour one tablespoon of batter in each paper cup.
2. Arrange them on  a microwave safe plate and microwave on high for 2 minutes.
3.  Allow to stand for 5 minutes.
4. Serve.

title: La Historia de Papa John's
description:
Cuando estudiaba en la secundaria y trabajaba en un local de pizzas en Jeffersonville, Indiana, el fundador de Papa John's, John Schnatter, sintió que a las cadenas nacionales de pizza les faltaba algo: una pizza tradicional, de calidad superior entregada en la puerta del cliente. Su sueño era algún día abrir un restaurante que llenara ese vacío.

En 1983, John se llevó su título en administración de la Ball State University y regresó a Jeffersonville, Indiana. Allí, a los 22 años, tiró abajo un armario de artículos de limpieza que estaba en la taberna de su padre (Mick's Lounge), compró equipo usado de cocina por un valor de $1600, y comenzó a vender pizzas en el fondo del bar.

Desde el primer día John supo que podía hacer una mejor pizza usando masa fresca e ingredientes de calidad superior, y se negó a abandonar ese compromiso con la calidad. Funcionó, y a la gente le encantó su pizza. En 1984, John abrió su primer restaurante Papa John's, y Papa John's se ha ido fortaleciendo desde entonces. Actualmente, Papa John's es el reconocido líder de la categoría de la pizza y ahora tiene más de 3,500 restaurantes propios o franquiciados en 50 estados y 29 países. Más de 25 años más tarde, hay algo que sigue igual, Papa John's aún cumple con el eslogan de la marca: "Mejores Ingredientes. Mejor Pizza."

"Hacer una pizza de calidad usando mejores ingredientes ha sido la base de Papa John's por más de 25 años. Me comprometo a que Papa John's no se desvíe de la base de calidad y superioridad sobre la cual se construyó la empresa. Siempre nos esforzaremos por ser su 'Mejor' empresa de pizza".

title: Trauzeuge gesucht! Deutscher Trailer
description:
Trauzeuge gesucht! Deutscher Trailer Trauzeuge gesucht! (Original-Titel: I Love You, Man!)
Ab 23. April 2009 im Kino.

Mit "Trauzeuge gesucht" stellt Komödienspezialist John Hamburg (Regisseur von "... und dann kam Polly", Autor von "Meine Braut, ihr Vater und ich", "Meine Frau, ihre Schwiegereltern und ich" und "Zoolander") seinen neuesten Spaß vor. Peter Klaven (Paul Rudd aus "Beim ersten Mal", "Jungfrau (40), männlich, sucht ..." und "Vorbilder") ist ein erfolgreicher Immobilienmakler. Kurz nach seiner Verlobung mit seiner Traumfrau, der bildschönen Zooey (Rashida Jones aus "The Office"), entdeckt er zu seinem Entsetzen, dass er keinen einzigen Freund hat, den er zu seinem Trauzeuge machen könnte. Peter will diese Situation schnellstmöglich ändern und lässt sich auf eine Reihe höchst bizarrer und peinlicher Dates mit anderen Männern ein. Bis er Sydney Fife (Jason Segel aus "Nie wieder Sex mit der Ex") kennenlernt, einen charmanten, eloquenten Mann, mit dem sich Peter sofort blendend versteht. Doch je besser sich die beiden miteinander anfreunden, desto mehr leidet Peters Beziehung mit Zooey. Schließlich muss sich Peter zwischen seiner Verlobten und seinem neuen Kumpel entscheiden. Was sich als gar nicht so einfach erweist in dieser verrückten Geschichte, die sich mit viel Humor damit auseinandersetzt, was es wirklich bedeutet, miteinander "befreundet" zu sein.

Darsteller:
Jason Segel, Paul Rudd, Rashida Jones, Jaime Pressly

title: Breaka TV Commercial - Aussie Pete
description:
Aussie Pete at just 17 years of age, 80s hairstyle and all. This TV commercial for Breaka flavoured milk, was the most expensive ad ever produced at the time in Australia and was more like a huge budget mini film. In terms of $$ per second, it cost more to make than a full-feature film.

The commercial, the first for the then new beverage and the begninning of a long-running campaign (It's a Dream of a Drink'), ran for 5-years across all TV stations in prime time and in cinemas along with all new releases... it got so that I could not walk the streets of Brisbane without being recognized as 'the Breaka Boy'.

The pretty models sourced for the ad, were Australia's best and most well-known, and some people old enough to remember might recognize one as the drummer from the popular 1980s all-girl band, Sheeba (hope I spelled it correctly).

The video here is a conversion from the original VHS video to digital (thanks to my brother, Michael) of the one minute version of the commercial, along with a current affairs story (Brisbane's State Affair) covering the 'behind the scenes' and interviews with producers and directors.

Finally, if you stay watching long enough, somehow a small snippet from my DJ days (no sound) at Manhattan nightclub - the largest and most popular venue at the time - regularly at least 2000 to 3000 patrons on any night of the week - owned and run by my then bosses and good friends, Gerry Bellino and Vic Conte, who were portrayed in the fourth series of 'Underbelly'. (It was the 'in' place in it's day).

Not surprisingly, I was known in my DJ days of the 1980s, as 'Breaka'... a nickname long since forgotten.

The attached is a very rare 'blast from the past' - enjoy!!

BREAKA - IT'S A DREAM OF A DRINK....

title: THE LOST MEMOIRS OF TOUCAN SAM
description: Toucan Sam was a lover, a father, and a commercial star. It seemed he was at the top of the world, until his addiction to Froot Loops began to interfere with his work, and even his family. None of this was helped when his wife, Toucan Samantha, was shot by robbers in 1992. His sons tried everything, but Sam was descending into a downward spiral of depression out of which none could revive him. This is the lost tape of a 1993 interview, just weeks before his tragic death, that details the events of the last few months of his life.

title: VIDEO Ini Membuat Jutaan Orang Menitikkan Air Mata
description:
"Cinta yang tidak bisa dibeli dengan uang"/"Katresnan sing ora bisa dituku karo duit"/"Loves what money can't buy."
Setiap harinya, pria tersebut selalu berbuat kebaikan yang sama. Mulai dari membantu seorang ibu mendorong gerobaknya, memberi makan anjing, diam-diam memberi buah kepada seorang nenek tua, hingga memberikan uang kepada pengemis.

Ia juga memberikan bangkunya di bus kepada seorang wanita. Satu sikap yang cukup langka di kalangan anak muda saat ini. Meski demikian, kebaikan sang pria tak jarang membuat orang-orang yang melihatnya menggelengkan kepala.
Di akhir video sang pria mendapatkan balasan dari kebaikan hatinya. Ia memang tidak menjadi terkenal dengan berbuat kebaikan, namun pria tersebut menerima cinta dari orang-orang yang dibantunya. Cinta yang tidak bisa dibeli dengan uang.

title: Australian television commercials from 2002
description:
A collection of advertisements recorded from Channel Nine Brisbane (QTQ9) in August 2002.

One of the adverts that may stand out in this video is the "New Myer Centre" commercial near the end. The Brisbane CBD shopping centre had undergone renovations from 2000-2002, with the closure of notable Brisbane nightclubs Metropolis and The Funkyard in the centre's bottom floors, as well as the closure of the amusement park Tops which was located in the top level. The bottom-level cinema was replaced with a Target store, and was relocated to the top floors, replacing Tops.

This video has been uploaded for nostalgia and educational purposes. If anyone has a problem with it being uploaded to Youtube, please contact me.

title: Closing to 10 to Midnight- 1983 MGM/UA Home Video edition
description:
Copyright Disclaimer: Under Section 107 of the Copyright Act 1976, allowance is made for "fair use" for purposes such as criticism, comment, news reporting, teaching, scholarship, and research. Fair use is a use permitted by copyright statute that might otherwise be infringing. Non-profit, educational or personal use tips the balance in favor of fair use.

After the conclusion of the end credits, we get something rather unusual. First, the copyright screen is in a font not often seen on MGM/UA or even MGM/CBS videos in 1983. Second, there is a short end clip promo. This version is slightly different than the one that appears at the end of 1984/85 print year MGM/UA tapes. This one proudly announces the creation of the MGM/UA Entertainment Group in 1982! A real rarity to see this variant.

title: De onde vem? | De onde vem o sal?
description:
Ao chegar em seu lar doce lar, Kika começa a desejar algo açucarado para comer. Por sorte, sua mãe está lá misturando vários ingredientes, como farinha, leite e ovos, na preparação de um bolo. Mas, chega a hora do açúcar e Kika resolve se questionar: de onde ele vem? Assim, ela fica sabendo que ele vem da cana, que é cortada, colhida e moída. Mas o processo não é só esse e o próprio pote de açúcar é quem explica tudo à ela.

Como toda criança, Kika tem perguntas de sobra sobre o que acontece ao seu redor. Mas não é sempre que os adultos estão prontos para responder de forma satisfatória tudo que Kika precisa saber, mesmo  que os assuntos sejam conhecidos. A série "De onde vem" aproveita esses  momentos para contar, em uma linguagem simples, divertida e acessível, tudo que a garota quer conhecer:  o ovo, o sapato, o espirro, o livro, o fósforo, o plástico, o choro, a energia elétrica e a onda.

Disponível para download no site: www.dominiopublico.gov.br

title: Disney Channel Junction - 1995
description:
From 1995, a few promos from Disney Channel, one of those networks that changed so much that constant comparison is made between its old and new incarnations..  The BEAUTIFUL ident/lineup dates to 1991 I think, and was used to introduce the night time lineup.  It's always been one of my all-time favorite branding pieces.

I hate to be the one to throw cold water on nostalgia, but old-school Disney Channel was frankly never that great.  I mean, look at this junction - Disney World infomercials, history documentaries, teacher awards, country specials.  Kids programming wasn't that great either - old, forgotten imports, old Disney afternoon series, you get the idea.  Oh, yeah... and this was a premium channel that you had to pay to see.

If I had to pick between this and the current, teen girl focused Disney, I'd pick the latter.  Because, unlike here, there's at least programming somebody would watch.

title: How the Best Advertising Campaigns Tap Into the Story of the Underdog
description:
http://602communications.com. Everyone loves cheering for the little guy. In this three-minute emotional marketing lesson video, emotional marketing expert Graeme Newell shows how some of the world's best advertisers tap our love of the underdog, then attach that feeling of transcendence to everyday products.

What is customer focus? It's how the best advertising campaigns use core emotional drivers to connect with their customers on a significant, meaningful level -- and Football provides a perfect place to do all that and more. As Graeme Newell points out in this short marketing video, Football fans love the game for a lot of reasons, most of which have nothing to do with the sport itself. The idea of a scrappy, tough kid working harder than everyone else and achieving fame and glory lies at the core of the experience.
Positioning a brand to fit that same attitude is the essence of what we do here at 602 Communications. We hone in on the best advertising campaigns and best television ads to find out what your customers love. Football doesn't take a lot of special gear.  It's a sport where even the poorest kids can triumph. Mediocre advertisers will seize upon the glory and fury of Football, but the best advertising campaigns will show the self-made man who clawed his way to the top by sheer force of will. With this focus acquired, we can start to cultivate a real relationship with the customer.
What is customer relationship marketing? It's how customer-focused brands show that they share the same values and passions as their customers. Football fans are passionate about the Cinderella story -- rags-to-riches paved with blood, sweat and tears. Customer relationship marketing is honing in on that feeling. Deep in our hearts, most of us believe we're an undiscovered star, and that we work harder and longer than most people.  Maybe we too can get the big promotion, find love, or achieve greatness. The best television ads are the ones that leave the customer thinking: "Yea, they get me"
Once a brand has customer focus and customer relationship marketing at its core, it can begin to hand its brand over to the customer entirely. Positioning a brand by letting your most diehard fans decide what you stand for is as close to marketing perfection as it gets. When you have become a reflection of how the customer feels about themselves, all the powerful emotions they feel for the sports they love will be passed on to your brand. 
Nike's mastery of this technique is one of the reasons it is the household name it is today. It's elegant in its simplicity: build a brand on a universal human emotion and let the customers do the rest. People see the Nike brand and think: "That's totally me! Unlike everyone else, I had to work to get where I am today. I work harder, longer and stronger than those sissies." And we've been saying the same thing to ourselves for thousands of years -- it's a truly universal human emotion.
So to recap: what is customer focus? It's positioning a brand around the customer. The best advertising campaigns are the ones that are built from the customer up, not the product down.

What is customer relationship marketing? It's making the best television ads, and whatever else you can bring to the table, all revolve around building a rapport between your brand and the deepest emotions your customers feel.
Master these two techniques and you'll have a brand that truly belongs to the customer.
http://602communications.com

description:
FederalAutoLoan.com

Car Loans for First-Time Car Buyers

Has that rusted, torn-up, beater of a car that you drove all through high school and college finally collapsed? Are you in the market for a new car but don't really know where to start? Federal Auto Loan is the place for you! FederalAutoLoan.com is designed to help new and first-time car buyers get approved for car loans fast and easy with our online application process! With the help of Federal Auto Loan, you have a chance to get approved for a quality car loan fast through one of our lender or dealer partners!

A car loan is a substantial financial commitment; and it is a commitment that is often handled poorly by first-time car loan buyers. Don't get caught up in making the mistakes of others! A general rule to keep in mind is this: If you cannot squeeze your auto loan into 48 months, do not purchase the vehicle! If you do, you are headed down a path of destruction. In addition, it is also a good idea to put 20% down. It is a common statistical fact that many first-time car loan buyer who break one (or both) of these two rules runs into trouble with their vehicle at a later time. It is never a good idea to be in the position of owing more on your loan than your car is worth.

Having little to no credit history creates hassle for many first-time buyers trying to get approved for an auto loan. However, this is where Federal Auto Loan can help! Assuming you meet some general criteria, such as a steady income of $1600 a month or more and an established pattern of paying your bills on time, Federal Auto Loan can probably help get you approved for your first car loan, with our online process, in no time at all!

Whether you are in need of a new or used car for your first-time auto loan, FederalAutoLoan.com is here to assist you! By submitting a simple online auto loan application, Federal Auto Loan will submit your information through a secure connection to one of our lender or dealer partners, who will do their best to help you get financing. 

Financing your first car does not have to be a scary or tedious process. With the help of Federal Auto Loan you can save both time and maybe money as well on your auto loan. By using FederalAutoLoan.com, the tedious work of trying to find a dealer or lender to help you is done in advance! So what are you waiting for? We'll help connect you with a partner to help you get the financing you need. With Federal Auto Loan you'll see just how easy financing a car for the first time can be!

MTV3: KAIKKIEN AIKOJEN PARHAAT SEKUNNIT (HISTORY OF FINNISH TV COMMERCIALS) 

Kaikkien aikojen parhaat sekunnit on ohjelmasarja, johon on koottu suosituimpia mainoselokuvia 1950-luvulta 2000-luvulle. Ohjelmassa nähtävät mainokset on palkittu Mainos-Oskareilla, Kultaisilla Klaffeilla, Voitto-palkinnoilla tai muilla vastaavilla tunnustuksilla. Lisäksi mukaan on poimittu omien vuosikymmentensä muistetuimpia ja puhutuimpia mainoselokuvia. 

Osa 2/5; 1970-luku  
Merkkitavarat tulivat Suomeen. Mainonnalla luotiin brändeja jotka elävät edelleen. Pesupulvereiden tehoa todisteltiin testimonial-mainosten voimalla. Mustavalkoinen televisio muuttui värilliseksi. Tarjousmainokset tulivat ruutuun. Farkut ja jenkkipurkka valloittivat. Ajatar tuli Forumiin. Mainoksissa tarjottiin edelleen myös informaatiota.

title: Ny reklamefilm fra Friele Colombia
description:
Kaffehuset Friele har utviklet et nytt reklamefilmkonsept sammen med TRY Reklamebyrå.

Aksel Hennie har regissert denne filmen som er fortellingen om Flavio i Colombia. Flavio driver en liten kafé på landsbygden. Han lager både god kaffe og på en fantastisk måte, men det viktigste er kanskje at Flavio tar seg tid til å snakke med gjestene om deres små og store problemer. Og at det er mye som kan løses over en god kopp kaffe. 

Filmen er produsert av Håkon Øverås og Mette Waaberg i 4 1/2. Medvirkere har vært Egil Pay (AD) og Lars Joachim Grimstad (teskst), Kristin Berge Jahr (prosjektleder) og Monika Augustsson (konsulent).

Действительно, слава Тарантино не дает покоя молодым кинематографистам. Еще один английский режиссер создал культовый фильм, который за девять недель проката в Великобритании сделал огромную кассу. title: Knight Rider Inspired Commercial - Mike & GITT From OPET
description:
This is a Knight Rider inspired commercial for OPET - the biggest Turkish fuel oil distribution company in Turkey.
The main charakters are Cem Yilmaz as Mike and a talking car - G.I.T.T. You can easily recognize Michael Knight & KITT in them. :)
This is the first commercial, the begining. :)

Translation:
Boss: Mechanic Mike...
GITT: Mechanic Mike is out, who's asking?
Servant: Who's talking?!
GITT: I'm GITT, 'Güzel İnsan Taşıma Taşıtı' (Nice Person Carrying Vehicle).
Boss: Nice.
Servant: The car was talking?
Cem Yılmaz: Hello there.
Woman: Mr. Cem congratulations.
Man: Here, your crystal apple award.
Cem Yılmaz: Hold on what's the rush, we just started the ad. Let's cover this up so this isn't classified as an under cover (subliminal) advertisement, right GITT?
Servant: What did it say?
Boss: Whooowhoo.
Boss: If you're ready, lets go. Mike?
Cem Yılmaz: Let me slip into something more comfortable. Don't touch the car.

Boss: Our people are very uneducated and unaware of things when it comes to fuel consumption Mike. Traffic, the environment, you have a lot of work to do on these subjects.
Cem Yılmaz: Worry not! We will inform everyone! Right GITT?
Cem Yılmaz: It's me, it's me... alarm.
Boss: Anyway, this is your licence.
Cem Yılmaz: Nice.
Boss: These are your cards.
Cem Yılmaz: OPET cards. I will use these in future adventures.
GITT: Ooh, we're getting gas from OPET bro?
Cem Yılmaz: Sure thing son, OPET, your favorite. He goes nuts when he hears OPET.
Boss: Umm, before you leave I want to introduce you to someone.
Cem Yılmaz: Hopefully not someone unneccessary?
Boss: Our head technician, Banu!
Banu: Hello.
-Button on dash reads 'wedding', and the car 'dresses up' as a typical wedding vehicle in Turkey.
Cem Yılmaz: I hope you don't mind, he got a little excited and went into wedding mode.
Banu: Is that the case? I designed a watch for you. This watch will allow you to communicate with GITT.
Cem Yılmaz: Oh Really, doll (hands Banu the doll). Lets see if it works. What time is it GITT?
GITT: You got a watch on your hand bro.
Cem Yılmaz: Good, it works. Keep the doll. Ok then, may all of this be prosperous and benificial.

Narrator: A man. A car. A fuel giant.


To discuss Knight Rider visit http://www.knight-rider.pl/ with an international forum!

title: 和田アキ子「まさか来るとは」　 「進撃の巨人」CMに起用！　会見(1)
description:
★エンタメニュースを毎日掲載！「MAiDiGiTV」登録はこちら↓
http://www.youtube.com/maidigitv

歌手の和田アキ子さんが3月20日、人気アニメ「進撃の巨人」を題材としたスマートフォン向けゲームアプリ「進撃の巨人 -自由への咆哮-」（DeNA）の新CMに起用されることになり、東京都内で行われた発表会に登場した。以前からアニメの劇中に登場する巨人に「似ている」と言われていた和田さんだが「まさかCM出演の話がくるとは思わなかった」とオファー時の感想を語った。

「進撃の巨人」では初のスマートフォン向けゲームアプリで、巨人の侵入を防ぐため人類が築いた壁の外へと追放された者同士の生存をかけた戦いを描くバトルゲーム。新CM「現実の巨人　登場」編は、とある焼肉屋を舞台に「壁の上から超大型巨人が顔をのぞかせる......」という名シーンを再現したもので、和田さんは"現実の巨人"として出演しており、お笑いコンビ「カラテカ」の入江慎也さんと矢部太郎さんも登場する。

オファーをもらってから作品を見直したといい、「巨人が人間を食べるシーンとかあって、最初は"どうなのかな"と思ったけれど、とても面白かったし、引き込まれた」と語り、「『現実の巨人』って言葉って面白い。気に入りました。これから電話でも使っていこうかな『もしもし、現実の巨人です』って」とまんざらでもなさそうな表情。入江さんと矢部さんが巨人に対して恐怖するシーンについては「ふだんから私に対してビビッているので、あれは"素"」とからかった。

「現実の巨人　登場」編は21日から全国で放送。また和田さんは「現実の巨人　走る」編にも出演し、28日から放送される。

title: Comercial adidas Originals -  Star Wars™- Guerra de las Glaxias - Cantina 2010 - David Beckham
description:
El astro del futbol David Beckham se une al elenco de 'Star Wars' en un comercial de una marca deportiva.

Además del inglés, que no disputará la Copa del Mundo en Sudáfrica, para la campaña de Adidas participaron Noel Gallagher (Oasis), Ciara, Snoop Dogg, Franz Beckenbauer y el grupo francés Daft Punk.

Ambientado en una de las cintas de la exitosa saga creada por George Lucas, donde se mezclan escenas  del filme donde se observa a Han Solo (Harrison Ford) y Obi-Wan Kenobi (Alec Guiness), con las de las estrellas actuales, el anunció denominadp 'Star Wars Cantina 2010', es uno de los comerciales que la firma alemana lanzó de cara al Mundial.

title: Vintage KLFY TV-10 Video from Ca. 1968-75, Part One
description: This video comes from an old, battered VHS tape that belongs to my father, who worked for KLFY for decades.  It includes a montage a classic slides used for broadcast purposes, from the good old days when TV stations had their own in-house artists who painted and inked everything by hand.  Also shown are a number of bloopers, some vintage TV ads and at least one spoof ad.  Among the personalities appearing on the tape: Maria Placier, Jim Baronet, Bill Besson, Rod Bernard, Mike Barras, and Bruce Conque.  Part Two can be found here: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mK2noe38lWI&feature=g-upl

title: Candan Erçetin GİT Official Original Video Klip
description: Candan Erçetin "Kırık Kalpler Durağında" albümünün 3. video klibi GİT şarkısına çekildi. Erçetin'in 2. klibi "Kırık Kalpler Durağında" ve 3. klibi "Git" 'in klip yönetmenliğini Bozkurt Bayer ve Cihangir Ateşağaoğlu birlikte üstlendiler. Klibin görüntü yöne...tmenliğini ise Tolga Kutlar yaptı. "GİT" klibi son günlerde dünya sinemasının da kullanmaya başladığı, 35mm film dokusuna çok yakın görüntü elde eden yeni teknoloji Canon 5D Mark II fotoğraf makinesi kullanılarak çekildi. Sözleri Cemal Safi'ye, müziği Candan Erçetin'e ait olan şarkının çekimleri İstanbul'un çeşitli semtlerinde gerçekleşti. Evinden çıkıp bindiği arabasıyla, her şeyi geride bırakan bir kadını canlandıran Candan Erçetin, çoğunluğu şehrin merkezinde yapılan çekimlerde arabayı kendi kullandı. İstanbul'un hiçbir yolu trafiğe kapatılmadan gerçekleşen çekimler 3 günde tamamlandı.

title: Mes meilleures amies, bande annonce (2011)
description: Annie a la poisse. Son fiancé l'a quittée et son nouvel amant est un goujat. Lillian, sa meilleure amie, file quant à elle le parfait amour. Lorsqu'elle lui annonce son futur mariage, Annie oublie ses soucis pour se consacrer à son rôle de témoin et transformer les préparatifs en un moment magique et privilégié. Mais c'est sans compter sur les autres amies de Lillian, l'insatiable et athlétique dragueuse Megan, la candide Becca,l'ex-beauté Rita et l'ultra-snob Helen... toutes incontrôlables et décidées à donner de la voix pour imposer leurs choix dans l'organisation de l'enterrement de vie de jeune fille. Débute alors une délirante aventure...!

title: Smokey Bear Fire Prevention Public Service Announcements (PSA), 1971 - 1985
description:
This film was edited to remove countdown leader from between the Smokey Bear PSAs. The content of the PSAs has not been altered.

Creator(s): Department of Agriculture. Forest Service. (07/01/1905 - ) (Most Recent)

Series : Forest Service Public Information Films and Public Service Announcements, compiled 1945 - 1995
Record Group 95: Records of the Forest Service, 1870 - 2008

Access Restriction(s): Unrestricted
Use Restriction(s): Restricted - Possibly
Note: Some or all of this material may be restricted by copyright or other intellectual property restrictions. The use and reproduction of the Smokey Bear symbol is restricted by Public Law 82-359, as amended by P.L. 93-318, Title 18 U.S.C. 711, and 36 CFR 271.

Scope & Content: This film consists of several PSAs. The first opens on a dark screen with the words "a personal viewpoint". Ray Charles explains the different sounds he loves to hear in the forest and cautions viewers: "Please be careful with fire, because when we lose a forest we lose a lot more than meets the eye. The second PSA shows a close-up on an animated Smokey Bear as he says, "Next time you're in the forest do me a favor." Long shot of the word, THINK, with Smokey and a pine sapling replacing the letter I. "America the Ugly" shows a forest fire. The camera then zooms out until the fire is revealed to be a reflection in the left eye of a costumed Smokey Bear. Smokey looks at the camera and says, "Only you." "Mask" shows a lit, wooden match as it falls onto a group of matches arranged in the shape of the continental United States. All of the matches are then consumed by the fire. "America the Beautiful" is playing in the background. Over this singing a narrator states that "one careless second with a match and America the beautiful becomes America the ugly." "If you knew it was me would you have listened?" begins with a close-up of the face of a young, blonde woman. She cautions viewers to be careful with fire in the forest in order to prevent forest fires. Extreme close-up of her face and hair as she tilts her head down; a costumed Smokey Bear raises his head making it appear as though the woman's face was only a mask that he was wearing. Smokey says, "If you knew it was me would you have listened?" "I think I love You Smokey Bear" shows a female singer on stage with a microphone as she sings part of the song: I think I love you Smokey Bear. At the conclusion she walks over to a costumed Smokey Bear and strokes his cheek. "Little Fire" shows two young boys as they threw a lit match into dry brush; a hiker tossing a lit cigarette aside; a burning campfire with a car driving away; and an unmonitored trash fire. These images are juxtaposed with images of a raging forest fire. A narrator states that "Nine out of ten forest fires are caused by little fires." In "Wristwatch" there is a close-up on a Smokey Bear wristwatch with Smokey Bear painted on the face. The second hand begins at 10 and ends at 12. A narrator states, "By the time the second hand reaches 12, forest fires will have burned down another 100 trees unless you help." "Careless" begins with a light brown background and then an outline of a pine tree appears as if being sketched by an unseen hand. A flame appears and follows the path of the outline, consuming it. "Please help prevent forest fires" appears at the bottom of the screen. A narrator states that "It can take nature one hundred careful years to grow a tree, but man can burn it down in just one careless second. Please help prevent forest fires."
